title: dottie's bean salad
directions: Drain beans well. Toss beans, celery, green pepper and onion together in a large bowl.
Thoroughly mix sugar, oil and vinegar. Pour over vegetables, tossing with fork evenly. Cover and set in refrigerator for at least 8 hours, tossing several times during this period.

title: pizza burgers
directions: In large bowl combine meat, 1/2 cup pizza sauce, pepperoni, Parmesan cheese and seasoning mix.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil or grill to desired doneness, basting frequently with remaining pizza sauce.
Top each piece with cheese slice. Broil or grill until cheese begins to melt.
Serve on toasted Italian bread.

title: witches brew
directions: Simmer milk, sugar and cinnamon sticks in a saucepan. Combine coffee and cocoa mix. Add to milk. Keep warm in coffee pot on stove.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika, salt and pepper. Brown in hot oil in Dutch oven or large pan. Add water and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender. Place mushrooms, onions and carrots over and around meat.
Pour in tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add parsley or celery leaves just before serving. Remove from heat and gradually stir in sour cream. Serve with small cooked noodles.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan as you preheat oven to 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over melted butter.
Drop fruit over top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: beverly slimm's puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to a boil over medium heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from the heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cook until almost softball stage.
Mix all well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice and put in top of double boiler.
When hot, add the following, mixed together:
eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook until thick and then let stand until cool; fold into fruit and last, fold in whipped cream.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight is better.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour; mix well.
Beat egg yolks. Add yolks, milk and butter to first ingredients.
Cook until thick; add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a kettle, simmer for 3 hours. Skim fat from soup.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add parsley and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Press 1 pound hamburger in dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of onion soup mix on top of hamburger.
Then press the remaining pound of hamburger on that.
Sprinkle the remaining onion soup mix on top.
Cook Kluski noodles 5 or 10 minutes; drain.
Add 2 cans of tomato sauce to noodles.
Pour that over hamburger mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
(Cover while baking.)
Top with Colby cheese and bake 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: pizza dip
directions: Take as many avocados as you can afford; peel and mash, adding a little lemon juice to keep it from darkening.
Then add to taste:
chopped onion, chopped tomato, mayonnaise, garlic powder, salt and Tabasco.
Stir and enjoy.

title: summer pasta
directions: Toast walnuts in SilverStone skillet until toasty and brown. Turn out of skillet and set aside.
To same skillet, add chopped onion, garlic and water (or wine).
Simmer gently until onion is very tender.
Stir frequently.
Add tomatoes (if fresh are used, chop fine; no need to peel).
Simmer about 5 minutes to reduce liquid.
Add basil and mint.
Continue to simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring water to boil in large pan to cook pasta (salt water).
Cook pasta per directions on package.
Drain well in colander.
Turn into pasta dish.
Pour sauce over and toss. Add walnuts.
Sprinkle with Parmesan or if you like, 3 ounces of dried Feta can be added on top.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken diane
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Coat chicken completely with mixture.
Place in a 350° oven, covered, for 20 minutes.
Turn and baste and bake until done, about 10 minutes.

title: rosemary-garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Scrub potatoes.
Peel away a strip of skin around center of each.
Toss potatoes with rosemary, butter or margarine and olive oil in medium size baking pan to coat well. Roast 35 to 45 minutes until potatoes are tender, turning gently every 10 minutes.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.

title: crab supreme
directions: Split the English muffins and you may toast them before adding topping.
I find it works all right either way.
This is best, of course, with fresh crab.
However, imitation crab works well. Celery should be chopped very fine and I like to use much more (say up to 3/4 cup).
Mayonnaise is just enough to moisten. Combine all topping ingredients except the cheese.
Spread topping on English muffin and then top with 1 to 2 thin strips of Cheddar cheese.
Broil until heated through, not too high on broiler rack. Serve immediately.
Nice with a tossed salad for lunch.

title: turtles
directions: Arrange groups of three or four pecan halves 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Top each group with one caramel.
Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until caramels soften.
Remove to waxed paper and flatten caramels with spatula.
Top each turtle with one milk chocolate square while still warm.
Spread when melted. Makes 4 dozen turtles.

title: pineapple marshmallow pie
directions: Heat pineapple juice. Add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows have melted. Chill and beat 1 cup Pet milk until thick. Combine with above ingredients. Put into large graham cracker crust and chill.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and measure. Add 1/2 cup sugar and sift to mix. Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Add cream of tartar.
Beat until egg whites are stiff.

Sprinkle remaining sugar over whites, 4 tablespoons at a time. Beat for 25 strokes after each addition. Beat in flavoring. Fold in flour mixture by fourths (fold in with 15 strokes). Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn upside down to cool and remove from pan only after completely cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Drain off most of the oil in the salad dressing, using the seasonings at the bottom of the bottle.
Mix all ingredients together, putting the tomato in last.
Salad can be made the day before and refrigerated.
A good hot weather dish because there is not mayo to spoil.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish; dump in pineapple. Sprinkle flour and sugar over top of pineapple. Sprinkle on cheese. Top with cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot potato chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve warm.

title: squash fluff
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix with cracker crumbs, milk, salt, pepper, sugar and squash.
Fold in eggs.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish.
Bake for an hour at 350°.

title: stir-n-roll pizza dough
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together in bowl.
Make well in flour, put in milk and oil.
Stir with fork, then knead with hands. A 9 x 13-inch pan or pizza pan makes this crust, then add your sauce and toppings.
Bake for 15 minutes, then add cheese.
Bake five minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: peanut soup
directions: Saute the onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in the flour until well blended.
Add the chicken stock, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat and puree in a food processor or a blender.
Add the peanut butter and cream, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to low heat and heat until just hot, but do not boil.
Serve garnished with peanuts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add pineapple and juice to bread cubes in 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve hot or cold.

title: steak rolls
directions: Place 1 strip of bacon and onion on sirloin tip and roll up, secure with toothpick; brown.
Cover with mushroom soup and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and Cheddar cheese soften and mix together with deviled ham.
Put into refrigerator until it gets firm. After it firms, roll into large ball and cover it completely with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate or lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and flour until well blended.
Mix sour cream, Ricotta cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla; add to first mixture. Last beat in one egg at a time into mixture, using 4 eggs.
Pour mixture on top of cake mix and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Turn oven off; let stand for 1 hour.
Bake in lasagna pan.

title: lentil stew
directions: Wash lentils, drain and set aside.
In a pot, place garlic, onions and green pepper with some water.
Steam.
Stir about 5 minutes until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, basil, oregano and thyme.
Stir in lentils.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 to 50 minutes until lentils are tender.
I like this on a sandwich.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and add sugar; cook together for about 10 minutes.
Add jello.
Pour into jars.
Makes approximately 3 pints.

title: beef in wine
directions: Mix onion soup, mushroom soup with water and cooking wine and pour over roast.
Cover and put in oven at 350°.
Cook until tender.
May have to add a little broth or water.
May also add other spices.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Combine jelly and mustard in crock-pot; add sausages.
Heat on high for about 1 hour, then simmer.
Serve from pot.

title: true southern corn bread
directions: You will need one iron skillet.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Saute peppers and onions in a little butter.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Add peas, mushrooms, peppers and onions, then add cheese (just break or cut in small pieces). Stir until cheese begins to melt.
Add chicken.
Pour in pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This serves about 15 people (may be frozen before cooking).

title: german chocolate chess brownies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Pat in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chocolate mix and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Arrange Twinkies in a pyrex dish. Pour strawberries (with juice) over Twinkies. Slice bananas and make a layer over the strawberries.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Drain Veg-All.
Mix Veg-All and Cheez Whiz and put in casserole dish.
Dot with butter, then top with Ritz crackers or onion rings.
Bake at 375° until browned on top.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in pie crust.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses stand to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together; form into a ball.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: easy chocolate chip cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding as directions on the package in a big enough pan so the cake mix will fit in after. Take pudding off stove and mix in chocolate cake mix as is.
Mix with pudding, it will be thick.
Almost like a brownie.

title: barbecued salmon
directions: Rinse salmon and pat dry. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Mix well and brush over salmon. Place salmon on an oil grill over medium heat for about 5 minutes per side, basting with butter. Fish is done when it reaches an internal temperature of 150° and flakes easily when tested with a fork. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy; beat in the oil.
Add sugar, chocolate and flavoring; fold in dry ingredients.
Squeeze excess moisture from zucchini and add to mixture.
Blend in dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in preheated oven.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: tuna meltaways
directions: Heat broiler. In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except muffins. Mix well. Divide tuna mixture evenly into muffin halves. Place on broiler pan 4 to 6-inches from heat. Broil for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly. Serve warm.

title: apple or peach crisp
directions: Place apples or peaches in a greased 5 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Slice mushrooms thin; saute in butter or margarine for 3 minutes.
Add onion, meat or fish, sprouts and seasonings.
Add this to the well beaten eggs; blend well.
Drop from large spoon into frying pan with about 1/4 inch of hot fat.
Brown one side; turn and brown other side.
Serve hot with Chinese Sauce.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, salt, shortening, mincemeat, vanilla and flour.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: creamy onion and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and next three ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cover, reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk and heat thoroughly.

title: ms. smiths' candy
directions: Add peanut butter to melted chocolate.
Stir to blend.
Pour over all the other ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Drop on wax paper by the teaspoon.
Allow to cool.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: peanut butter chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in cereal and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: choucroute garni
directions: Soak sauerkraut 5 minutes in cold water and drain well.
Place ham hocks in Dutch oven or large heatproof casserole.
Add drained sauerkraut, wine and bay leaf.
Press cloves into onion; press onion down into sauerkraut.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer very slowly 1 1/2 hours, tossing with a fork once or twice, or until ham hocks are almost tender.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender.
Refrigerate. Keeps well for a long period of time.

title: onion meatballs
directions: Form hamburger into 5 or 6 good sized balls.
Roll in flour and salt and pepper mixture.
Brown balls in pan with a little oil to keep from sticking.
Add chopped peppers and onion soup.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage.
Remove core and boil until tender in salted water.
Set aside.
Wilt onion in melted butter.
Add cheese.
When melted, add soup.
When blended, add boiled cabbage and mix well.
Add spices.
Put into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and beat together.
Add applesauce.
Place dry ingredients in sifter together; beat well. Add raisins and mix together.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 16 muffins.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pour into oblong cake pan.
Blend together remaining ingredients and pour on top of layer in pan.
Don't mix together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chess bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg. Press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: old time buttermilk pie
directions: Use 9 in pie plate; Bake crust at 350° until it just begins to brown.
Cool.
Cream butter & sugar well; Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla, and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° at least 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, eggs and 3/4 bag of Mozzarella cheese together.
Cook meat.
Drain grease.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer. Cook noodles until tender.
Put layer of meat, 3 noodles, another layer of meat, layer of cheese mixture, layer of noodles, meat, cheese mixture and the balance of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni and add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in the soup, milk, mushrooms and peas.
Add the drained tuna fish. Cut the cheese slices into small pieces and stir into the mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, beaten egg, salt, pepper and half a can of tomato sauce.
Combine remainder of sauce and rest of ingredients.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini as per package directions.
In pot, melt butter, but don't burn. Add cream to warm, but not boiling.
Add drained tortellini to butter and cream mixture. Toss to coat. Add Romano and toss to coat all over. Serve right away. Great with Italian or garlic bread and salad.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: In a large bowl, combine buttermilk, sugar and salt.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot water.
Add to buttermilk mixture.
Mix well.
Mix in pineapple and lemon juice.
Pour into ice cream machine and freeze according to directions.
If using freezer method, pour into pans or undivided ice cube trays.
Cover and place in freezer.
When mixture reaches mushy stage, transfer to bowl and beat with mixer to minimize ice crystals forming. Return to trays, cover and freeze until frozen.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: grandma sweet cream
directions: Cut biscuits into pieces and dispose them in deep large plate. In a pan combine sugar, yolks, milk and Porto wine.
Stir over low heat, mixing well with wooden spoon.
As soon as it boils, remove from heat and pour over the biscuits.
Garnish with cinnamon or chocolate powder.

title: apple pie
directions: * May use 4 or 5 peeled and sliced fresh apples.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with foil (for easy cleaning).
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls using a heaping tablespoonful of mixture for each.
Place 1/4-inch apart in the lined pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until brown and no longer pink in the centers. Makes 32!

title: microwave candy bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a large bowl suitable for the microwave oven.
Microwave on High for 1/2 minute after mixture comes to a rolling boil. Remove from oven.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir well. Add Rice Chex and peanuts.
Put into a buttered pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: spiced tea
directions: Fill coffeepot with cranberry juice cocktail and apple cider or apple juice.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: s'mores
directions: Roast marshmallow over fire until toasty.
Place between graham crackers and chocolate.
Squeeze.
Eat and enjoy.

title: south of the border chili
directions: In large 5-quart Dutch oven, brown pork in 2 tablespoons oil. When meat is brown, push to side of pan and add 1 tablespoon oil and 1/4 cup flour.
Brown, then add 2 to 3 tablespoons chili powder and cayenne pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add 2 1/2 cups warm water; mix well.
Add beans.
Stir.
Add water until pot is almost full.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Then reduced heat to low and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May add additional chili powder or cayenne pepper to taste.
Stir frequently.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and sausage.
Drain well.
Add grated cheese, chopped chilies and tomatoes.
Cook until well blended.
If too thin, sprinkle with flour and stir until right consistency.
Serve warm with corn chips. Makes 3 quarts.

title: my mom's quick saturday night supper(coney island hot dogs from leftover spaghetti sauce)
directions: Punch holes in aluminum disposable cake pan.
Fit cake pan into a saucepan so that cake pan rim (only) sits on rim of pot and lid will cover it.
Leave no holes where steam can escape except the ones you punched in cake pan.
Put hot dogs in pan; fill with water and boil dogs.
Mix chili powder with spaghetti sauce and cook on low fire about 15 minutes so flavor will go through sauce. When hot dogs are done, lift lid and lay rolls in cake pan to steam (about 1/2 minute).
Prepare with fixings and serve with baked beans and potato chips on paper plates.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of oblong dish.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients, except crumbs, and put in cracker bed. Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: pork chops in wine sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter until brown.
Remove onions and brown pork chops which have been sprinkled heavily with flour, salt and pepper.
Pour wine mixed with soy sauce over chops.
Cover and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crescent tuna cups
directions: Combine all ingredients (except rolls) together.
Place crescent rolls in muffin cups.
Drop tablespoons of mixture in each.
Close the crescent roll.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Let set 5 minutes before removing.

title: chilled vegetable soup
directions: Mix together juice, water, broth mix and lemon juice.
Add the veggies to the juice. Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 5.

title: grandma gwen's swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in half the milk for 1/2 hour.
Mix ingredients in order, with remaining milk last.
Oil your fingers and shape to desired size (1 pound of meat will give you approximately 60 small party meatballs); roll in flour (or sprinkle a little on) and fry lightly at medium heat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange in layers the butter, broccoli, cheese and crackers. Repeat.
Sprinkle rest of cheese crumbs on top.
Drizzle on butter.
Pour on milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs with all other ingredients.
Pour in a casserole dish and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Grate cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple-glazed pork (rib) chops
directions: Combine apple juice, brown sugar, mustard and cloves in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add chops; seal bag and marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours, turning bag occasionally. Remove chops from bag, reserving marinade.
Place chops on a broiler rack coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place rack on broiler pan.
Broil 5 1/2-inches from heat for 9 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, basting frequently, with reserved marinade.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and coffee.
Stir in jam.
Bake in 3 greased 8-inch layer pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not overbake.
Cool and frost.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water as per directions on package until done. Scald milk and mix with cooked rice.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add 1/2 to 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and cold milk.
Add the cold mixture to rice mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick; stir often.

title: enchilada bean casserole
directions: Butter large size pan.
Put 6 tortillas in pan.
Brown meat; season with salt, garlic salt and chili powder to personal taste. Spread meat over tortillas; add chopped onions and spread.
Spread beans over this layer.
Slice cheese and layer over beans.
Top with remaining 6 tortillas.
Spread condensed soup over tortillas. Spread with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: whole wheat pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients.
Knead until soft.
Rest in a warm place until twice the size.
Cut into 16 strips.
Roll.
Cover and let rise until twice the size, approximately 45 minutes.
Bring 2 quarts of water with 4 teaspoons baking soda to a boil.
Turn to light simmer.
Gently place pretzel in water with slotted spoon. Leave in water 1 minute, turning once.
Remove and place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with coarse salt, poppy seed or sesame seed, if desired.
Bake at 475° for 12 minutes.

title: homemade pizza(serves 2 to 4 people)
directions: Make pizza crust according to directions.
Use a deep dish 10 x 10-inch pan for thick crust or a cookie sheet for thin crust. Generously grease sides and bottom of pan.
Form dough to pan. Spread on pizza sauce.
Too much sauce makes sloppy pizza.
Top sauce with all other ingredients.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a small bowl.
Use to marinade chicken for 3 to 4 hours.
Then heat to a boil and simmer for a few minutes.
Pour over rice.
Recipe is meant for 2 servings, but can easily be doubled or tripled for larger servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in large casserole.
Add cracker crumbs, then oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ginger-orange carrots
directions: Place carrots in pressure cooker.
Blend all other ingredients.
Pour over carrots and cook 3 minutes.
Cool cooker at once.

title: russian cabbage rolls
directions: In water to cover, boil cabbage to limp stage; cool and separate leaves.

title: baked greens(swiss chard, spinach or mustard)
directions: To cook, place greens with just the water which clings to leaves in saucepan.
Cover and cook 3 to 10 minutes for spinach; 15 to 20 minutes for Swiss chard and mustard.
Drain thoroughly and chop.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place greens in ungreased baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches.
Arrange water chestnuts over greens; spread soup over top.
Bake 25 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk and lime juice.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: middle eastern chicken
directions: Heat the olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute chicken breasts 5 to 8 minutes per side, until meat is white throughout.
Remove chicken to a plate.
Add the onion and garlic to skillet and stir-fry a few seconds.
Add
the cumin powder to taste, 1/2 cup chicken broth and 1/4 cup currants; simmer about 2 minutes.
Remove pan from the heat and whisk in 1/2 cup plain yogurt and chopped mint.
Add the chicken and reheat slowly without boiling.
Serves 4.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all in blender.

title: pastry shells
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt into pie pan.
Mix milk and oil together.
Pour on top of flour mixture and mix with fork. Press into shape of pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Simmer until ready to use.
Good for chicken or ribs.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, melt butter. In a separate bowl, mix flour and 1 cup sugar until well blended. Add milk and mix until blended.
Pour this over butter; do not stir.
Pour blackberries over this; do not stir, then sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over berries; do not stir. Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: noodle and meat casserole
directions: Cook chopped meat in frypan until brown.
Cook noodles until soft.
Put chopped meat and noodles in casserole dish. Combine with spaghetti sauce, salt, pepper and minced onion.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour in preheated oven.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute onions, green onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic in margarine until wilted. Add crawfish tails and seasonings. Saute for 5 minutes. Add golden mushroom soup.
Heat over medium heat until simmering; do not boil. Serve hot on Ritz crackers.

title: jelly roll
directions: Line an 18 x 10-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Put out on a towel and spread jelly all over and roll up in a big roll.
Don't cut until cool.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening and butter with electric mixer; add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with damp cloth until ready to use.
For best results, keep icing bowl in refrigerator when not in use.
Refrigerated icing in an airtight container can be stored 2 weeks.
Re-whip before using.
Yields 3 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables, chips, seafood or baked potatoes.

title: saucy jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and mix in applesauce until mixed. Chill until slightly thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mold and chill.
May be served on greens.

title: mighty good salad
directions: Cut in small pieces and season well with salt; mix with salad dressing.
Garnish top with pimientos.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to directions on box, being careful not to overcook so they will hold together while you stuff them.
Set aside.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together in a plastic bowl. Place melted butter and milk on top. Do not stir. Cook 2 minutes, uncovered, on full power. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir and pour in a greased dish.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients with 1/2 cup flour. Mix next 5 ingredients in rest of flour and stir in cracker crumbs.
In another large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks and beat until fluffy.
Add cracker crumb mixture, blend well and stir into fruit mixture with juice.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in cracker mixture, turn in well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated slow oven at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Insert toothpick to see if done, cool in pan for 1/2 hour.
Loosen in pan and turn on rack to cool.
Garnish with candied fruit and wrap in foil to store.

title: peach bowl
directions: In a decorative glass bowl, layer fruit.
Pour orange juice over mixture, cover and let marinate in refrigerator for two hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cube the cake and place in a trifle dish or large glass bowl. Layer with mousse, then Cool Whip and then the candy.
Repeat the process.
Chill and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck and cook according to instructions on taco seasoning package.
Drain and set aside.
Mix sliced tomatoes, cucumber, onion and lettuce in large salad bowl.
Add ground chuck and cheese.
Top with Doritos.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from canned fruit, adding water, if necessary, to make 2 cups liquid.
Stir fruit, liquid and pudding mix together.
Allow to set until pudding consistency.
Serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Drain juice from beans.
Stir in pepper, onion, tomatoes and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: classic apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with rolled pie crust; spread filling evenly in crust.
Place vented or lattice top crust over filling.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; serve as a dip with small crackers or vegetables such as cauliflower, carrots and celery. Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef patties with gravy
directions: Brown meat patties in a skillet.
Add 1 can of beef broth and simmer until done.
Thicken broth with water and cornstarch mixed together.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Measure flour, soda, spices and salt; sift together 3 times. Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in applesauce.
Add flour mixture in 3 portions, beat after each addition until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan or bake in greased muffin pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
This cake or muffins have improved flavor after 2 days.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat ingredients and spread in quiche dish or pie plate.
Pour bottled pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sliced green onion, 1/2 cup chopped green pepper and sliced pepperoni (cut in small pieces).
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken and bone it.
Cut it into small pieces.
Save broth.
Bring milk, butter and chicken broth to a boil.
Put chicken in mixture and simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: easy chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef; season with salt and pepper.
Add bell pepper and onion; cook until tender.
In large kettle, mix beans, tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and Chili-O mix.
Add meat mixture and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place gingersnap cookies in food processor or blender.
Process until fine crumbs.
Transfer to bowl.

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with tomatoes, green peppers, black olives, onions and French bread.
(If double the recipe, only use the 2 sticks of margarine.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook and debone chickens.
Simmer ham bone in water to cover for 3 hours.
Cool and take off fat from chicken and ham broth. Mix chicken and ham broth.
Dice onions, potatoes and celery and add to broth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and let simmer 45 minutes.
Add Tabasco sauce and sugar to taste.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add garlic salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes until meat is tender.
Add green pepper and continue cooking until it is tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except rice, and stir into meat mixture.
Cook, uncovered, until broth is clear and thickened.
Stir just enough to prevent sticking.
Serve on rice.
Yields 6 servings, 2/3 cup sauce and 1/2 cup rice each.

title: parmesan cheese
directions: Remove skin from chicken; rinse and pat dry.
In a plastic bag, combine Parmesan cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
In a shallow dish, stir together egg and milk.
Dip chicken into egg mixture.
Place 2 or 3 pieces at a time in the plastic bag.
Close bag and shake to coat chicken with cheese mixture.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: easy dip
directions: Chop green onions into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk, pumpkin, pudding and spice. Mix slowly with mixer until blended; fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm (4 hours) or overnight.
Then refrigerate before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together.
Add enough pineapple juice to thin mixture for easy dipping.
Serve with strawberries, pear slices, oranges, pineapple, apples, grapes, kiwi, etc.

title: nita's fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and season, then fix eggs, milk and baking powder.
Sometimes I coat the chicken before I pass it in the egg batter and then again after I batter the chicken.
Put in hot oil and cook until golden brown.

title: s'mores
directions: Yields 4 cookies.
For each cookie, arrange 1 graham cracker in center of paper napkin or paper towel; top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Cover with graham cracker and wrap in napkin. Arrange on glass oven tray.
Heat at High 3/4 to 1 minute.
To complete, let stand 2 minutes before unwraping.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix sour milk or buttermilk with baking soda.
Add to cream mixture, then add eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and baking powder.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix a chocolate cake mix per directions and pour over.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Drop this by teaspoonfuls onto cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golf balls
directions: Melt chocolate and wax together. Roll balls in chocolate mixture.

title: lemon sponge
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat egg yolk and add lemon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold whites into rest of ingredients.
Put into crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 or more minutes.

title: caramel sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. In microwave, bring margarine, oil and water to boil. Pour over dry ingredients and mix. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Beat well. Pour in greased and floured sheet cake pan, 11 x 15 x 2. Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Pare carrots and cut into thin strips.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cook carrots in bouillon covered for 10 minutes.
In another saucepan, melt butter; add onions and cook, covered, 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in next 3 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add carrot mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add pinch of sugar.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Heat tomato soup, oil, vinegar, sugar and dry mustard until sugar is dissolved. Pour over carrots. Add sliced onion and marinate in the refrigerator for a few days.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ground meat and minced garlic.
Pat into a round 12-inch pan to form crust.
Mix tomato sauce and seasoning.
Spread over hamburger crust.
On top, add onion slices, cheese slices and drained mushrooms.
Sprinkle top with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake with oven temperature at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender.
Add melted butter to Cheez Whiz, then fold in carrots.
Pour into baking dish; top with onions.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes, or until onions are browned.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown meat with pepper and onion; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except buns; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pudding cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Saute onion and bell pepper. Put all beans (undrained) in slow cooker.
Add beef, onion, bell pepper, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Cook 3 hours on low.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping; to remaining cake mix, add egg and 1/2 cup oleo.
Mix by hand.
Press in bottom of well greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine pumpkin and other ingredients; pour over cake mix.
Mix reserved 1 cup cake mix with sugar and softened oleo (not melted).
Mix by hand and sprinkle over top of pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto a pizza pan.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Salt and pepper the fish, inside and out.
Melt margarine and add chopped onion and celery.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add bread cubes and mix.
Add enough water to moisten the bread and stuff the fish with this.
Skewer bacon slices on the fish with toothpicks and place it in a well-greased baking dish.
Arrange carrot and onion slices around and on the fish.
Add chicken broth and wine.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until the fish flakes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and lemon juice.
Spread in bottom of 8x8x2 inch glass dish.
Mix together brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes until bubbly.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream. Six servings.

title: easy tasty asparagus tips
directions: Spread asparagus tips in pan; cover with Velveeta cheese slices and sprinkle with bacon bits on top. Put in oven at 400° until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and seasonings; set aside. Cook spaghetti as directed;
drain.
Turn
into	a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Beat
eggs;

over
spaghetti.
Pour butter over top
and
sprinkle	with
Parmesan cheese.	Spread with cottage cheese.
Add cooled meat mixture; pour sauce over meat
layer. Top
with
Mozzarella cheese.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and beaten eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk; add to egg mixture alternating with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Use 1/4 cup measure to pour dough for each cookie. Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 11 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen large cookies.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel onions and chop coarsely.
Saute onions in butter 15 to 20 minutes until clear.
Stir in milk.
Put 1/2 the onion mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 the cracker crumbs and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat; ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Chill.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix spinach, cheese and onions.
Add flour, salt and oregano. Mix.
Add butter, eggs and milk.
Stir.
Bake in large 9-inch dish at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon together in a small shallow dish. Open biscuits and separate. Cut each into half, then into half again. Roll in sugar cinnamon mixture. Place in a greased bundt pan, layering till all pieces are placed in pan. Combine butter, brown sugar, and water in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring well. Cook for 2 minutes. Pour over biscuit pieces. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Place serving plate over top of baking pan and invert. Pull apart pieces to serve.

title: pork chop and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil in a large skillet for 3 minutes on each side.
Remove.
Add onion rings to fat remaining in skillet; saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove; reserve.

title: dilly mashed potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, cover potatoes with water.
Cook until very tender.
Drain and mash with milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chile con queso
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Add chilies and tomatoes, breaking up tomatoes with a spoon.
Lower the heat and add both types of cheese and cook until melted.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook until all ingredients are heated, but do not boil.
Makes 4 cups.
Dip can be used as a sauce over meat.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Heat a large skillet or wok with oil until just begins to smoke.
Add broccoli and cauliflower stems only and saute for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining broccoli, cauliflower, celery and onion. Stir and saute for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 cup water and cornstarch which was already added to 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and allow to cook 2 to 3 more minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, brown half the meat at a time in hot cooking oil; drain off fat. Transfer meat to crockery cooker.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add egg and milk and beat until smooth.
Heat 1-inch oil in skillet or plug in deep fryer.
Put finger over small hole of funnel and pour 1/4 cup batter into it. Remove finger to release batter into oil.
Begin at center and move out.
Fry 2 minutes, turning as necessary.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with fresh fruit or cinnamon.

title: chicken liver spaghetti
directions: Heat oil and brown chicken livers quickly on each side. Remove from pan.
Reduce heat and put onion in pan.
Cook on low heat until soft, but not brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Stir.
Add chicken livers and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Pour French dressing over warm potatoes; chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onions, eggs and salt.
Add mayonnaise and mix carefully. Add 1 teaspoon celery seed, if desired.
Chill 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in corn muffin mix.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: curried meatballs
directions: To this pan
blend in flour and slowly add consomme.
A cup of water

gravy is desired.	Add tomato paste
and	curry
powder.	Add
meatballs to gravy and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: thelma's italian beef
directions: Place meat in covered roaster and add all other ingredients. Bake 3 1/2 to 4 hours at 350°, covered.
Remove meat and cool in refrigerator.
When chilled slice about 1/4 in. slices and return to broth that has been strained and heat to serve.

title: mom's never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening.
Put egg and vinegar in a one cup measuring cup and blend.
Fill cup to full with cold water.
Stir into flour mixture.
Bake for about 10-12 minutes or use as directed for pie recipe.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow the shrimp soup to thaw and the cream cheese to reach room temperature.
Then mix all ingredients well.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Set cream cheese out until room temperature.
Cook the marshmallows and 7-Up over medium heat until melted; add the lime jello.
Add this mixture slowly to the room temperature cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add the pineapple and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in the Cool Whip and beat thoroughly. Pour into mold or serving bowl and chill.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add butter, eggs and vanilla. Stir until moist.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: pizza spins
directions: Brown beef and sausage, drain well.
Add Velveeta cheese and spices.
Spread a heaping tablespoonful on each slice of cocktail rye bread.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread with peanut butter chips
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Blend pumpkin, oil, water and eggs; stir in chips.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix juice with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts and freeze.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and chopped garlic.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Fill casserole with alternating layers of sauce, noodles and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put oleo in pan and melt.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pan of butter.
Pour fruit in center.
Cook at 450° for 25 minutes or until brown.
If fruit is not very sweet, add another 1/2 cup of sugar.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs and then mix all of the ingredients, except for the brown sugar and walnuts. Mix brown sugar and walnuts. Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Pour 1/2 the batter into the Bundt pan, spread the brown sugar and walnuts on top of the batter. Pour the rest of the batter in the pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Put a cooling rack over the Bundt pan, turn over and remove the pan.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then broccoli, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce.

title: pizza
directions: Mash with hands and put on pizza pan.

title: impossible lasagna
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Place in oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, hot water and butter in large bowl until butter is melted. Stir in stuffing crumbs just to moisten. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt margarine and add to the other ingredients.
Pour in baking pan and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: escalloped apples
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and flour; toss with apples in a plastic bag until well coated.
Place in a casserole coated with vegetable spray.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vicky's egg rolls
directions: Mix well.
Spread over the period of a lifetime.
Serve generously to everyone you meet.

title: microwave twice-baked potatoes
directions: Wash and pierce baking potatoes.
Wrap each in paper towel and microwave on High 32 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and carefully scoop cooked potato out of shells.
Be sure to leave a thin wall of potato around the shell to ensure durability of the shell.
Mash potatoes and stir in milk, butter, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in chopped chives, 1/2 of the crumbled bacon and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.
If mixture becomes too dry, add more cream, butter or sour cream (your preference).
Place potatoes halves in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and fill with potato mixture.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until hot, turning dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Remove and sprinkle remaining cheese and bacon over top and let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce date cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In small bowl, combine flour, rolled oats, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves; set aside.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Cut shortening into all the dry ingredients. Add dissolved yeast and buttermilk. Stir well, place in air tight container and refrigerate. Take out as you need and roll out on floured board. Cut and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake 15-20 min. at 400°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add rice, soups and mushrooms.
Mix well. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar and butter in large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy. Mix in dry ingredients, alternating with chocolate and corn syrup.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add chopped nuts and pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Makes 20 pieces.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine nuts, dates and cherries in a bowl.
Sift salt, sugar, flour and baking powder; add nuts, dates and cherries and stir until well covered.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in fruit mixture until well mixed.
Turn into greased wax paper-lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions.
Mix first 6 ingredients together and fill cooked noodles with mixture. Pour a little spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place filled noodles over top.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over top of noodles.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Make into balls.
Roll into sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt.
Let stand overnight; drain well.
In a saucepan, cook sugar, cornstarch, celery seed, mustard, turmeric, ginger and vinegar over medium heat until fairly thick.
Add zucchini mixture and the peppers.
Continue cooking until thick.
Then boil 1/2 hour, stirring frequently. Place in sterile jars and process 1/2 hour (pint jar).
Makes 8 to 10 jars.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Heat butter; add squash, onions, salt, pepper and tomatoes. Cook covered until squash is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese; heat until cheese is melted.

title: a b c dip
directions: Stir well and blend all ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with any crackers or chips.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in lard until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add egg and just enough water to make a stiff dough.

title: rosemary's beer batter
directions: Mix eggs and beer well and then add remaining ingredients. Do not overmix.
Deep fat fry at 375°.

title: sweet-sour barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1-quart measuring cup, mix together all ingredients. Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
Spread over chicken or pork and bake, grill or microwave until meat is done.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Saute onions and pepper until soft.
Stir in pineapple juice, tomato sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Pour sauce over pork chops.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix the flour and sugar together and the lemon juice and rind, egg yolks, butter and salt.
Stir in milk and mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated london broil
directions: In large Ziploc food bag, combine all ingredients and squeeze bag to mix ingredients well.
Add steak, seal bag and lay in pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Flip over after about 3 hours so meat gets evenly marinated.

title: velvety chocolate cream pie
directions: Prepare shell; cool.
Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan. Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring until mixture boils; boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour in shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours and top with whipped topping.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, syrup and salt and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from
heat.
Add
vanilla
and soda.
Pour over popcorn and coat
well.
Bake
in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: slim dilly dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shake well.
Serve over salad greens. Makes 1/2 cup.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Place vegetables in layers in buttered baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Dot with butter. Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well and pat out on board.
Cut in shape desired.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together with spoon; stir until thickened.
Mix in sour cream and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and filling mixture.
Use remaining Cool Whip for the top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Chop chillies and onions.
Slice black olives.
Shred both of your cheeses.
Layer your ingredients as they are listed.
Heat until bubbly at 350°.

title: orange peach cake
directions: Beat.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan,
bake at 350°
for 35 minutes, or until done.

title: northern bean soup
directions: Put ham bone in pot.
Cover with water.
Add spices and beans. Cook one hour and then add vegetables.
Cook 15 minutes.
Then add barley.
Cook until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Press into casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda; add eggs, pineapple, flavoring and nuts and mix well.
Grease and flour sheet pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed chicken bake
directions: Prepare rice, using package directions.
Cut up chicken to bite size and season with salt and pepper.
Place in skillet and brown slowly in butter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and pecans. Melt butter and add to the mixture. Add pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°; let cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Slowly cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add soup, milk and tuna; mix well.
Cook noodles according to directions on package and drain.
Alternate layers of noodles and soup mixture in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with potato chips and return to oven to brown chips.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: To make corn juice, blanch approximately 1 dozen ears of fresh corn.
Barely cut tops of kernels off and scrape remaining pulp off cob into kernel tops (or can use canned cream-style corn).

title: my father's homemade sausage
directions: Mix together and make patties.

title: pear and cream cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into gelatin.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in a buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Arrange broccoli florets over rice.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and half of the cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked ziti
directions: In large saucepan, add olive oil, onion and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add tomatoes, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and baking soda.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook 1/2 pound Rigati (as package says).
Remove casing from sausage.
Cook until done.
Drain.
Add to pasta, Ricotta cheese, tomato sauce and sausage.

title: spaghetti boloney casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti until nearly tender.
Dice boloney and onions. Combine all but cheese in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese or buttered crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: sunshine fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease or Pam spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Fold in fruit mix; spread in pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons oats.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
May be frozen.
Makes 20 bars, each containing 120 calories, 49 grams fat and 10 milligrams cholesterol.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In medium pan, combine cocoa, sugar, brown sugar and salt. Add milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, still stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Let cool 5 minutes in pan.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into jars with tight fitting lids.
May refrigerate up to 1 month.
Makes 2 1/2 cups; 75 calories per tablespoon.

title: spicy cabbage rolls
directions: Remove 10 large outer leaves of cabbage; cook in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes or until just tender; drain and set aside.
Reserve remaining cabbage for other uses.
Combine next 8 ingredients.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold 2 opposite ends over and place rolls, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: old fashioned brownies
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, eggs, butter, Nestle Choco-bake and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: butch's cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in cake pan.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine nuts and coconut; spread in bottom of cake pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour onto nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs, molasses and dry ingredients.
Last, add soda to hot water and mix.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cherry mash
directions: Boil sugar, marshmallows and milk for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cherry chips.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and nuts.
Pour over cherry mixture.

title: maple rolls
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Roll out 1/3 inch thick.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up; cut. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut pecan squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well. Press into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs. Add light brown sugar and beat until thick.
Add pecans and coconut which have been tossed with 2 tablespoons flour.
I usually add a little more coconut! Add vanilla and salt; mix well. Spread over baked crust and bake 20 more minutes until browned. Sprinkle powdered sugar when cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate mousse in 5 minutes
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl; stir and let stand 1 minute to soften.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved (mixture must be clear).
Stir together sugar and cocoa in small, cold mixer bowl; add heavy cream and vanilla.
Beat at a medium speed until stiff peaks form; pour in gelatin mixture and beat until well blended.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill about 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice-raisin hot cereal
directions: Bring water to full boil with dash of salt.
Add white rice (Mahatma brand is good) and margarine or butter.
Immediately turn temperature down to simmer.
Cook rice for 20 minutes.
Add raisins and as much milk (1 to 2 cups maximum) as you like, plus approximately 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Heat just until hot, not boiling again.
Serve immediately.

title: toothpaste
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to make a paste.
Can also add less water and a little peppermint flavoring.

title: savory ground stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pan; drain.
Combine stew vegetables and 2 cups of water to beef; cook over medium heat. Add tomatoes.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, brown sugar and extract until smooth.
Spread mixture on small serving plates. Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until top is brown).
Serve with salad.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 55 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except cinnamon and add to cooked rice.
Cook and stir until thick, about 2-3 minutes.
Pour into a serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream cheese and add all ingredients.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Drain peaches; dissolve jello, sugar and spices in boiling water.
Stir in 3/4 cup peach syrup and vinegar.
Chill.
Add peaches.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix; store in refrigerator.

title: spirit cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in all ingredients.
Fold in nuts (optional). Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Allow hash browns to thaw slightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour can of Durkee French fried onion rings on top and bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir on low heat for 25 minutes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
After candy is set, cut and wrap in wax paper.

title: raspberry walnut torte squares
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour, confectioners sugar and butter; blend well.
Press mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together, by hand, do not use mixer:
flour, sugar, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and nuts.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube or Bundt pan.

title: apple rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Roll piece of apple in each; put in pan. Pour orange in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over top.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and oleo until boiling.
Cook until soft ball stage; stir.
Remove from heat; add all ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan; cool!

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash peppers; remove stems and seeds.
Grind peppers; add salt.
Mix and let stand 3 hours; drain.
Add vinegar and sugar; simmer slowly until the consistency of jam, about an hour.
Pour in small jars and seal.

title: open-faced sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, together.
Cut bread into desired shape; spread mixture.
Great finger food.

title: white fudge
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook and gently stir to 236°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and let cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick and not glossy. Add 1 cup broken nuts, if desired.
Spread in buttered pan.
Chill and cut into pieces.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: apricot or peach danish
directions: Blend butter, sour cream, flour and salt; chill for 1 hour or overnight.
Divide into 2 parts; roll out each into a rectangle about 12 x 6-inches.
Spread dough with about 1/2 cup jam lengthwise to within an inch of edges.
Fold dough in half lengthwise and seal edges.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.
Cut into 1-inch strips to serve.

title: wieners in a cup
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Roll out biscuits and put in tins. Mix pork
and beans, wieners, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion. Put
ingredients
in biscuits.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix together above items in a kettle with a lid.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over noodles. Serves 4.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid; add cold water so liquids equal 1 cup.
Stir Jell-O and boiling water until completely dissolved (about 2 minutes).
Stir in the juice/cold water. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours until slightly thickened.
Mix in the Cool Whip with whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Stir in oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serves 10!

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in juice.
Sift together and add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
MIx with hands the raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Add to mix. Divide dough in half.
Roll out each half on lightly floured, cloth-covered board into a rectangle and cut in 2-inch strips. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.
These can be iced and decorated with candied fruit while warm.
Cut baked strips into bars.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients but pecans and parsley.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Sprinkle parsley flakes on ball.
Add parsley sprig for garnish.
Serve with crackers.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix separately flour, sugar, baking powder, and milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter. Do not stir.
Heat fruit and pour over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes until brown.
Serve warm.

title: restuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes; take out insides.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble. Fry onion in bacon grease.
Add grated cheese, bacon, onion and sour cream to potatoes and put back in shells.
Bake at 300 or 325° until warm.
Also sprinkle with a little paprika.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sugar until blended.
Add about 1/2 cup beer and add more as needed.
Makes a wet tacky dough.
Spoon dough onto a floured surface.
Dust with flour.
Pat out to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut out biscuits.
Cover bottom of pan with shortening.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: moravian cookies
directions: Melt the shortening and margarine and add to sugar.
Stir in the molasses (real bubbling hot, very dark Puerto Rican molasses) and the soda, dissolved in boiling water.
Sift
about 4 pounds of flour with spices into the molasses mixture.
The dough should be almost stiff enough to roll.
Let it sit out overnight to blend flavors.
Roll on cloth covered board as thin as possible.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes, maybe less.
Makes 7 to 8 pounds of cookies.

title: marinated green tomatoes(makes 8 to 10 servings. prep: 15 minutes. chill: 1 hour.)
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices. Arrange half of slices in a large shallow serving dish; sprinkle with half each of sugar, salt and pepper. Top with remaining tomato slices; sprinkle with remaining sugar, salt and pepper. Drizzle vinegar evenly over tomatoes. Cover and chill 1 hour. Turn tomato slices, coating with vinegar mixture, before serving.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mash or slice fresh strawberries or use frozen ones.
Heat rhubarb to boiling and stir in strawberries.
Add salt and sugar. Stir well and add jello.
Taste to be sure it is sweet enough. Cool in fridge until thick as egg whites.
Stir well so fresh berries are all through the filling.
Pour into pie shell, then cool until firm.
Top with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients with spinach and chill for 1 hour.
Roll into bite sized balls and place on cookie sheet (can be frozen at this point).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 25 to 40.

title: good beef stew
directions: Cook beef until tender; add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until all is well done.
You may add a little more water as it cooks.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: lentil and sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage in a 3 to 4-quart pot over medium-high heat 3 to 5 minutes, breaking up with a wooden spoon until lightly browned. Drain and discard fat.
Add broth, water, lentils, tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until lentils are almost tender. Stir in pasta.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes until lentils and pasta are tender.
Stir in spinach and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer until tender.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery in small amount of butter until soft and tender.
Combine all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup crushed cornflakes.
Put this on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zesty wild rice salad
directions: Combine wild rice, shrimp, broccoli, cauliflower, cheese and peppers in large bowl.
Cover; refrigerate.
Just before serving, toss gently with dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased pan and put in freezer.
Cut into squares when frozen and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: cream cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in slightly salted water until fork-tender. Drain and mash with electric mixer adding the cream cheese and sour cream. Salt and pepper to taste, plus add milk as needed to make the potatoes smooth, but not soupy.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased or Pam sprayed glass baking dish.
Dot the top with butter or margarine.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fix ahead chicken
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with 6 slices of bread cubes.
Mix next 6 ingredients and spread on top of bread.
Add rest of bread on top of mixture.
Pour eggs, mixed with milk.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered 15 minutes at 325°.
Then add soup, cheese and almonds.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: southern rice
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add celery, green onions and green pepper; saute until crisp-tender.
Stir in broth and next 3 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Spoon rice into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add hot broth mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, and oil into a dough. Knead 4 minutes.
Let rise (rest) 5 minutes.
Roll out on cookie sheet.
In the middle 1/3 of the dough, top with corned beef, sauerkraut, then cheese.
Cut edges in 1-inch strips and crisscross over filling.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pecans, corn syrup and softened margarine in ungreased round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Spread to cover bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; beat 30 seconds. Spread over pecan mixture.
Bake until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan to loosen; immediately invert on heatproof serving plate.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Heat
sugar
and Karo until sugar is dissolved.
Do not cook. Stir
in
peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop on waxed paper in 1-inch balls.
Let cool and serve.

title: hot buttered rum batter
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter.
Add the ice cream and spices to taste.
Mix with mixer until smooth and well blended. Store in freezer.
To drink, heat water to boiling.
Add 2 tablespoons boiling water to 1 mug of batter; stir in 3 tablespoons rum.
Great on cold winter nights.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly. Then boil without stirring to 234° (soft-ball stage). Bulk of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Do not stir. Cool at room temperature to 110°. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Quickly spread in a lightly buttered 8 or 9-inch pan. Cool and cut in squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) pans. Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Blend in eggs. Combine cocoa, flour, powder, soda and salt in a bowl. Add milk.

title: lemon or orange sauce
directions: Boil water, syrup and cornstarch, mixed with a little cold water.
Boil 5 minutes and add fruit juice and 1 tablespoon caramel, if dark color is desired.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Slice tenderloin as you would pork tenderloin.
Wash two or three times.
Drain real good.
Take each piece and tenderize each side, then roll both sides in flour.
Put in oil and fry.
Sprinkle with salt on each side and sprinkle with paprika.
Fry on medium heat.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Pour 2/3 of soup/water mixture into large pan (9 x 13 or larger). Mix mayo, chicken and stuffing together and stuff shells. Pour rest of sauce over shells and top with cheese. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sally lunn
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Put the two yeast cakes in the cup of warm milk.
Add the milk and yeast cakes to the creamed mixture along with flour and salt.
Let dough rise in a warm place for several hours.
Beat the dough down and shape into to loaves.
Let dough rise again until doubled in size.
Bake in a moderate oven about twenty minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, place in greased casserole, put 1/2 cup of noodles on top and bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Serves 6.

title: quick fudge cake
directions: Melt margarine,
cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and
pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir, then pour
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan (does not need greasing or flour).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pollo confughi
directions: Put olive oil and garlic in pan; brown lightly. Add cut up chicken. Brown and cook until there is no pink or 3 to 4 minutes. Add mushrooms and saut for about a minute. Take all out of pan and put aside. Add another tablespoon of olive oil and green onions to saut. Add tomatoes, oregano, pepper, salt and wine. Bring to a boil. Put on low fire and cook 15 to 20 minutes and add ham and parsley. Put on simmer for about 2 minutes. Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: grandma's caramels
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Then add corn syrup and mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring and cook to 245°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pan.
When cold, cut into squares and wrap.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Form about 1 teaspoonful dough into balls.
Grease cookie sheet. Press with fork.
Bake about ten minutes at 350°.

title: apple wedge cake
directions: Mix together.
Spread in a greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: On low heat in skillet add butter, celery and onion until onion is transparent.
Add to crumbs with lemon juice, minced parsley, rosemary, pepper, salt and Accent.
Toss lightly.
With fork, mix and add 1/4 cup hot water; set aside.
Rinse fish body cavity with cold water, drain and pat dry with backbone removed. Rub fish cavity with 1 teaspoon salt and 3/4 teaspoon Accent. Lightly pile (do not pack) stuffing into fish.
Fasten open edges with toothpicks.
Brush outside of fish with oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Makes 8 servings.

title: betty's cheese straws
