directions: Grate cheese and mix with margarine with hands until creamy. Mix until dough clings to bowl.
Grease cookie sheet and use cookie press.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add rest of ingredients.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350°.
Check for doneness after 45 minutes.

title: perfect icebox rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add boiling water.
When cooled slightly, add cold water.
Add beaten eggs and yeast (dissolved in lukewarm water).
Add salt to flour and sift into liquid mixture. Mix well but do not knead.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and on floured surface, shape into rolls (roll out and cut).
Put on cookie sheets and allow to rise for 2 hours.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Beat 5 minutes.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate nut cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease
baking
sheets.
Chop 1 1/2 cups of M & M's.
Reserve
remaining
whole
M & M's for decoration.
Stir together flour,
baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl cream butter
and
sugars.
Add	eggs
and vanilla; beat until light and
fluffy.
Add	dry ingredients gradually. Add chopped M & M's and
nuts.	Drop
on
baking sheets.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes.
Decorate cookies with M & M's.
Return to oven and bake for 3 to
5 minutes longer or until light brown. Makes 5 dozen.

title: kifles
directions: Combine sour cream and 1 tablespoon boiling water; mix well. Stir in package of dry yeast.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir until yeast is completely dissolved; set aside.
Place 1/2 cup softened margarine and 1/2 cup flour in small bowl.
Add sour cream mixture and beat 1 minute at low speed.
Add 2 egg yolks and 1/4 cup flour, beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Stir in enough additional flour (about 1 to 1 1/2 cups) to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide into 3 pieces.
Wrap with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours or up to 5 days.

title: mrs. marcia's cookies and just a few cookies
directions: Mix and roll out to the desired thickness.
Cut and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Add enough flour that the dough is not too stiff (a soft dough).
Roll on floured board and cut.
Bake at 350°.
Delicious!

title: fish on the grill
directions: Place fish in a glass dish and pour dressing over fish.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours (overnight, if preferred).

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix all together.
Microwave for 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes or bake in oven on low heat until golden brown.
Store in an airtight container.

title: tuna dip
directions: Place all but eggs in blender.
Mix in blender.
Then in blender chop in hard-boiled eggs.
Good for vegetables or chips.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese. Add sugar gradually, to cream mixture. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each. Add vanilla. Mix flour and nutmeg, add gradually to creamed mixture. Bake in lightly greased and floured tube pan at 275 degrees, starting with a cold over, for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: springtime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and chill in mold until firm.

title: hazel's sweet potato pie
directions: Wash sweet potatoes and boil until tender (remove skin).
Whip potatoes in large mixer bowl on high speed until fluffy.
Remove mixer beaters and rinse strings off beaters.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until they are stiff, not dry, peaks.
Slowly add 1 cup sugar, beating until meringue stands in very stiff, glossy peaks.
Spread over bottom and up sides of well-greased 10-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Beat egg yolks slightly in double boiler top.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Cook, stirring, until thick, about 10 minutes.
When mixture cools, whip the cream and fold custard into it.
Put in meringue shell.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat 4 egg white and set aside.
Beat the egg yolks in large mixing bowl.
Add milk and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Add melted shortening and mix well.
Fold in egg whites. Cook in waffle iron.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Cook corn bread.
Saute onions and bell pepper in stick butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Add cheese to top and bake 5 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Beat potatoes, butter and powdered sugar well.
Knead until satiny.
Add flavoring as desired.
Dip in melted chocolate.
This is filling for chocolate creams candy.

title: italian flag pasta
directions: Place the chicken breast in a medium saucepan and add enough chicken broth to cover.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender, about 12 minutes.
Remove chicken breast, cool, and cut into strips.
Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add the onion and saute until brown.
Add the mushrooms; cook, tossing gently, 2 minutes.
Stir in 8 Tbsp. of the butter, the ham, and the tomatoes.
Cook 6 minutes.
Stir in the chicken and cream.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Add the salt and pepper and keep warm over low heat.
Meanwhile, cook the fettuccine until just tender; drain.
Return the noodles to the saucepan and toss with remaining 1 Tbsp. butter.
Toss the fettuccine into the chicken-ham mixture.
Serve with parmesan cheese on the side.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Combine onion, brown sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix everything together and bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Let set in bowl in fridge 4 hours or overnight.
Pinch off dough and shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass dipped in cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 275° for 12 minutes or less.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add to jello.
Stir in.
Place in refrigerator for about 30 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip, then fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into salad mold.
Return to refrigerator overnight to set firm.

title: grilled toast with cheese
directions: In a large frying pan, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Place 2 slices of bread in pan.
Let brown; turn over.
On side facing up place one slice of cheese.
When other side is brown, put both slices together to form a sandwich.
Repeat for each sandwich.

title: baked tomato pasta
directions: Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise and set cut sides up in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix garlic, 1/3 cup parsley and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Pat mixture over cut sides of tomatoes.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons oil over tomatoes and bake at 425° until brown on top, 60 to 70 minutes. Boil spaghetti in 3 quarts water until barely tender to bite, 8 to 9 minutes.
Drain.
In a large warm serving bowl, combine butter, remaining parsley and oil, basil and 4 tomato halves that have been "skinned" (discard skins).
Coarsely mash.
Add remaining baked tomatoes and pan juices.
Gently mix with pasta, adding salt, pepper and cheese to taste.

title: hush puppies(serves 25 people)
directions: Mix thoroughly together and drop by tablespoon into hot grease.

title: grandmother's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan, then add cocoa until dissolved. Add milk and sugar.
Heat until it reaches a hard, rolling boil. Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter, then oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto sheet of waxed paper or foil.
Allow 10 to 20 minutes to cool before serving.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides at high temperature.
(Salt and flour before browning.)
Mix soup and spices together, and place with pork chops in a 9 x 13 inch pyrex dish.
Top with onion rings.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order as listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and
pineapple chunks.
Pour fruit into mixing bowl.
Add sour
cream;
mix evenly through fruit. Stir in remaining ingredients and chill for
to	4 hours in refrigerator.

title: hot cowboy beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer at least 4 hours, preferably 8.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter; add cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Stir in the vinegar gradually.
Continue stirring until the sauce boils.
Add the beets.
Keep warm until the sauce is a rich red.
Serves 6.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Place stick of butter on top of all ingredients in a casserole. Place in oven and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Stir once after margarine is melted. Mixture should be firm and slightly brown.

title: calico fruit compote
directions: In a small bowl, stir together lime or lemon juice, honey and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, layer apricots, strawberries, grapes and blueberries.
Pour honey mixture over fruit; toss gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate shortbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Combine butter, powdered sugar and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed scraping bowl often, until creamy. Reduce speed to low; add flour, cocoa and cinnamon. Beat until well mixed. Roll out dough on lightly floured surface, one-half at a time to 1/4 inch thickness (keeping remaining dough in refrigerator). Cut cookies with 2 1/2 to 3 inch cookie cutters. Place 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until set. Cool completely.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour.
Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board like biscuits.
Cut in desired shape and bake at 375°.
Done when brown.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain as much water as possible (press between paper towels) from spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and put in pie pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are slightly browned.

title: sunday stew
directions: Put all in crock-pot and cook one hour on high, then 8 hours on medium.
Serve with homemade biscuits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until done. Reserve 1/4 cup of broth. Chop chicken into small pieces; set aside. Combine crackers and melted butter. Reserve some for topping; place rest on bottom of casserole dish. Combine soup, broth and sour cream; mix well. Add chicken and mushrooms. Pour over crackers. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick beans and beef
directions: Brown meat and onion in large frying pan.
Drain if necessary. Pour in catsup.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and pork and beans.
Heat 10 minutes, or until mixture is hot and bubbling. You may add more or less chili powder.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Add salt. Let stand 1 hour and drain. Heat water, sugar and celery seed. Boil 1 minute. Cool to lukewarm. Stir in carrots, pepper, onions and drained cabbage.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together well the Cool Whip and cream of coconut.
Melt Cheez Whiz in small container.
Spoon small amount of cool mixture into Cheez Whiz and mix.
Pour together, mix and refrigerate. Serve with all types of fruit.

title: jean's sunday roast brown gravy
directions: In a frying pan put flour and brown until flour is done.
Add salt and pepper, as desired.
Add water.
Stir continually until mixed.
Pour or spread over roast and cook about 15 minutes or longer.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Use quantities according to size pot of soup you want.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Brown onion in butter or margarine.
Add all ingredients except frankfurters and simmer for 30 minutes.
Arrange frankfurters in shallow pan.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: lickety split cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Add sour cream.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Fill lined muffin tins 1/2 full, reserving 1 1/2 cups batter.
Make indentation in center of each cup with spoon and fill with preserves.
Spoon reserved batter over preserves, filling to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool completely and store in fridge.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Saute the bell pepper and the onion with the ground beef as it browns.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the meat mixture in the bottom of the pan.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients plus 1 cup water in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Uncover for 30 minutes and serve.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Sift ingredients into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes and in 1 hole, pour 3 tablespoons oil; in second hole, pour 1 teaspoon vanilla and in third hole, pour 1 tablespoon vinegar. Pour 1 cup cold water over and beat until smooth.
(You mix everything in the pan you are going to bake in.)
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with butter icing.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar, lemon and cinnamon sticks. Add remaining ingredients; simmer and enjoy. The alcohol burns off, leaving only the yummy taste.

title: oven-roasted shiitake mushrooms(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Spray a jelly roll pan or a baking sheet with sides with cooking spray or use a nonstick pan. Toss the mushrooms with the oil, garlic and salt. Place the shiitakes in a single layer on the prepared pan, caps up or down, it makes no difference. Just make sure that they have room to breathe. Roast, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven and shake a few times. Some of the mushrooms should be starting to get a little golden on the lighter underneath side of the caps. You will probably need to put them back in for a little longer, say 3 to 5 minutes, maybe more if your oven wasn't really hot when you put them in. You want at least a third of the mushrooms starting to turn a nice golden color on the gill side and getting a little crunchy. If you have used the lesser amount of oil, this will happen more quickly.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise, and scoop out.
Mash potatoes and lots of butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Scoop potato back into potato skins.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes longer.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil until onions are yellow.
Add ground beef and fry until mix falls apart.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While hot, poke holes in cake.
Pour frozen strawberries over cake.
Mix pudding according to box, then add cream cheese.
Spread over strawberries on cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spiced punch
directions: Place sugar and spices in basket of coffee percolator.
Put juices in pot and perk.
This is a delicious hot punch for the holidays.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, cocoa, sugar, Karo syrup, milk and yolks and cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with your favorite meringue.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured large fluted pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into lengthwise quarters.
Remove most of core. Keep the bundle of leaves together with a little of core.
Place in a bowl.
Cover with boiling water; drain after 10 minutes. Place cabbage in a small rectangular baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet; saute onion until soft.
Stir in the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with flour; cook for a minute, stirring.
Add broth.
Bring to a simmer.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Spoon over cabbage.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Baste a few times with sauce.
Remove from oven; thin sour cream with a little of the sauce.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder and add.
Add vanilla.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. You may double this recipe and bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with cooked broccoli (2 cups cooked rice on bottom before broccoli).
Cover with cut up chicken.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix water and bran.
Let cool.
Cream together butter and oil. Add buttermilk and honey.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.
Great for fast morning snack.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: With mixer, beat cream cheese, lemon juice and condensed milk. Use a large bowl for mixing ingredients. Beat until smooth. Drain pineapple chunks. Mix in Cool Whip and nuts. Mix all the ingredients well. Chill in the refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: luscious fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Gently fold in remaining optional ingredients.
Serve as soon as possible. (All fruit is optional.)

title: ginny's special dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of a deep pie plate.
Spread chili and salsa on top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of all. Microwave for 10 minutes, uncovered.
(Or can use in Corning Ware dish, covered.) Great dip for nachos.

title: toll house mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. In bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add egg; beat. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread onto foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle 2/3 cup chocolate chips over top; spread evenly.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop them.
Place them in bottom of baking dish.
Add cheese and mayonnaise and toss ingredients together.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Fold all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast or any of your favorite crackers!

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar in and set aside.
Meanwhile, bring vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.
Bring to boil again and pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate at least 2 days.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: seafoam kisses
directions: Combine sugar, salt and water in saucepan.
Place on heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and cook without stirring to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Pour syrup slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly until all syrup is combined.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until candy cools and holds its shape.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Nuts may be added.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and seasoned salt.
Put in chopped onion, tomatoes, beans and tomato sauce; add 1 can of water from each can of tomato sauce.
Stir well and cook until it comes to a hard boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion, shredded cheese, then the beaten egg and buttermilk; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening where fish are cooking.
When done, hush puppies will come to top.

title: colorful bean salad
directions: Mix beans, corn, pineapple (with some of its juice) and peppers (need not use all the peppers, especially if they are large).
Add vinegar and olive oil to taste.
Salt and pepper optional.

title: rum cake(improves with age!!)
directions: Mix all ingredients 4 minutes.
Spray Bundt pan well with Pam. (*Can sprinkle bottom of pan with pecans.)
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
While baking, prepare glaze.

title: cheese spread
directions: In a bowl, beat softened cream cheese and milk until fluffy. Add Parmesan cheese, parsley, onion, garlic, thyme and pepper and mix until well blended.
Spoon into small container; cover and refrigerate at least one hour.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, margarine, dry mustard and ginger; heat until all is melted.
Marinate chicken in sauce; arrange wings on cookie sheet.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Check to see if need turning.

title: baker's icing
directions: Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool. Add butter and shortening and blend at low speed.
Add salt.
Beat on high speed until smooth and fluffy.
Blend in sugar.
Beat at high speed until sugar crystals dissolve.
Add vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at high speed.

title: dream pie
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Beat until they form soft peaks.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Continue beating, adding sugar gradually.
Pour meringue into a greased 9-inch pie pan and spread it into a shell, 1/2 inch on the bottom and building sides to 1 1/2 inches.
Bake at 275° for one hour. Cool.
Whip the cream, adding the sugar and vanilla.
Pour into the cooled meringue shell.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. May add color, if you wish, with touches of strawberries or maraschino cherries.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Melt better in large skillet.
Saute garlic and ham for 2 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cook until crisp-tender.
Combine flour and cream; stir into skillet and blend well.
Add salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir one minute more.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under a preheated broiler until brown, 2 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: star cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining wet ingredients. Sift dry ingredients and add 1 cup at a time to wet ingredients. Roll into small balls and push candy down into dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Must preheat oven!
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients in order listed.
Pour into two well-greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: savory amish meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ingredients; form the mixture into a loaf. Put a few bacon slices on top and pour additional tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Mix well; roll in waxed paper.
Chill, then cut.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: In a 2 to 3 quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, 2 1/2 cups blackberries and salt over medium heat until berries make sufficient juice, then cook over high heat when mixture comes to full boil.
Have cornstarch
dissolved in 1/2 cup water; add to boiling berries, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and lemon juice.
Cool slightly; fold in 2 cups berries.
Pour evenly into pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining fresh berries over top, pressing in lightly.
When served, top with whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Stir in 2 cups water and Lipton soup mix.
Stir and cook for 15 minutes.
While sauce is cooking, boil noodles until tender.
Add sour cream to sauce and stir until creamy.
Add noodles and mix well.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice. Place in pastry crust. Dot with butter. Cover with second pastry crust. Pinch edges to seal. Make slits in middle of top.
Bake in hot 400° oven about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°; cook for about 40 minutes more.

title: potato-beet salad
directions: Dice beets and potatoes.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Allow to sit several hours before serving.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add to sugar mixture the coffee, glycerin and vodka.
Put in half-gallon jug.
Let set for 2 weeks.
Strain into smaller bottles for use.

title: sausage and bean casserole(microwave)
directions: Place onions in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Stir and re-cover. Reduce to Medium-high.
Microwave for 10 to 15 minutes longer, stirring twice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry pizza cake
directions: Butter 13 x 9 inch cake pan and pour pie filling in bottom. Sift cake mix over filling. Melt butter and pour over mix and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old settlers' baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, bacon and onion until meat is done and onion is tender.
Combine all remaining ingredients except beans.
Add to meat mixture; mix well.
Stir in beans. Place in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until heated through.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pastry mix *
directions: Sift flour and salt; blend in lard.
Store in covered container in a cool place.
Use 1 cup of mix for each crust.
Add just enough water to hold dough together.
For a very flaky crust, divide fat in half.
Cut in the first half of fat until mixture is as fine as meal.
Cut in the remaining fat until mixture is crumbled to the size of peas.
This recipe makes 11 cups of mix.

title: easy, cheesy corn
directions: Heat and drain.
Add butter and cream cheese; stir well.

title: almond pastry
directions: Bring to boil the water and butter.
Add almond extract.
Dump in flour and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour over the 2 strips.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until fork test is dry.

title: sue's turkish green beans
directions: In large pot, saute meat in butter until it changes color to gray or light brown.
Add onion and leave until they get limp. Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes or so.
Add beans and seasonings.
Cook on top of stove until beans are done.
Sprinkle pinch of sugar over top and several pats of butter while beans are cooking.

title: homecoming punch
directions: Combine sugar and 1 gallon water in pan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture is syrupy.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices, 1 gallon water and extract.
Let stand until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, pour 2 quarts mixture over crushed ice and add 1/2 quart ginger ale.
Yield:
75 servings.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir together well. Cover and cook 5 hours on high or 8 to 12 hours on low.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in a small muffin pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Place graham crackers on bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Slice 3 bananas and place on top of crackers.
Pour mixed pudding over it and add another layer of crackers, bananas and pudding, until gone.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix flour, salt, brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread 2 cups mixed nuts over crust.
Melt over low heat, 1 cup butterscotch chips, 1/2 cup syrup and 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour over nuts and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sugar-cookie hearts
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium-size bowl, with electric mixer, beat butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Beat in flour.
Refrigerate dough, tightly wrapped for at least 2 hours. Roll out dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with heart shaped cookie cutter.
Place cookies 1/2 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges just start to brown.
Makes 3 dozen 2 1/2 inch hearts.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put in 5 quart pan and add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jim's chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off any liquid.
Add all other ingredients, cutting tomatoes into smaller pieces, if so desired. Simmer for several hours adding tomato liquid as needed or desired.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix beef, spices, rice and onion well.
Form into meatballs, any size.
Put meatballs into covered pan or baking dish.
Add soup and water.
Bake in oven at 350° until meatballs are done. Tomato soup mixture will thicken like a gravy.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until coated; using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse rice well; set aside. Scald 4 cups milk. Skim off foam and add rice.

Add salt and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and remaining milk. Stir in raisins; mix well. Transfer mixture to a greased 2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook dried apples with enough water to cover.
Add sugar to taste; set aside.
Mix flour and Crisco together like biscuit dough until mealy.
Add water and buttermilk (May add more or less butter until dough is like biscuit dough.)
Knead dough; roll out thin. Use a saucer to lay on dough; cut a circle.
Put cooked apples on half the circle; fold other half on top of apple half.
Pinch together edges; prick middle with a fork.
Fry in Crisco oil that has covered the bottom of a pan.
Cook in electric skillet or iron skillet until brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cornmeal last.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: microwave chicken country captain
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Arrange pieces in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, with meaty portions toward the edges of the dish.
In mixing bowl, combine undrained tomatoes, pepper, garlic, raisins, tapioca, curry and thyme.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken. Cover with vented microwave-safe plastic wrap.
Cook on 100% power for 15 to 20 minutes; rearrange chicken after 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; place in baking dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and add 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers.
Place this mixture on top and bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
oil and eggs.
Beat well.	Alternate flour and milk.
Mix	well.
Add
coconut
and flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for approximately 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add vanilla extract.
Slowly add sifted flour; mix well.
Fill cookie press half full.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets using the star plate.
Hold press in semi-horizontal position and form wreaths by moving press in a circular motion.
Gently push ends of dough together to form wreaths.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 2 dozen.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together until blended well. Roll into balls and bake 250° for 30 minutes.

title: herb dressing
directions: Put all ingredients together and shake well.

title: whole stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage head 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool. Mix together other ingredients.
Peel back all leaves until the center of cabbage is exposed (about the size of a grapefruit). Cut this portion away.
Use half of filling to stuff center.
Roll enough leaves up to cover.
Use other half of filling and roll remaining leaves up.
Put the cabbage head and remaining leaves that have been rolled up into a baking pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Add 1/2 cup of water around cabbage head.
Cover and cook in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: graham cracker dream squares
directions: Place layer of crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1 cup butter, sugar, milk and egg in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbs, stirring well; remove from heat.
Pour crumb mixture over crackers.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Place layer of crackers over chilled mixture.
Combine remaining butter and powdered sugar, blending well.
Add small amount of cream until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Top cracker layer with powdered sugar mixture.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add green pepper, onions and dressing. Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon onto bottom half of toasted rolls and serve with wine vinegar to sprinkle over top of meat.

title: kurt's seven layer bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into small bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Add all ingredients except paprika and cheese.
Mix thoroughly; pour into greased, shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika over mixture. Bake at 350° until bubbly or around 30 to 40 minutes.
It can be frozen; remove from freezer at least 4 hours before heating. Yields 12 servings.

title: homemade vanilla extract
directions: Combine the brandy and vanilla in a fancy bottle with tight-fitting lid.
Cover and let stand for 3 months, shaking weekly.
After using about 3/4 cup of the extract, throw in a new bean and fill bottle up.

title: simple ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: cape cod clam chowder
directions: Steam clams.
Drain.
Remove from shells.
Cut clams fine with kitchen shears.
Cook potatoes until tender and yellowed.
In the top of a double boiler, melt butter over hot water.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk and cream in a steady stream, stirring to keep smooth.
Cook 8 minutes, until hot and thick, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and clams.
Cook just long enough to heat through.
Yields 1 quart.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter over top.
Bake at 350° in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: rice custard
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Add milk, vanilla and cooked rice; mix well.
Turn onto buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in glass pie plate.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Spread chopped chilies over chili.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over chilies.
Microwave on Medium until hot and cheese is melted.
Serve with nachos.

title: broccoli and mushroom bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute mushrooms and grated onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour, then milk, salt and pepper. Cook until thickened.
Put broccoli in large baking dish; pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 7 and is great for making ahead.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Combine broth and vegetables in a large pot. Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until veggies are tender. Melt butter in a Dutch oven over low heat. Remove from heat. Add flour, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Stir in vegetable mixture, soy sauce, cheese and chicken. Cook until cheese melts and mixture is heated.

title: chocolate zucchini squares
directions: Beat oleo, brown sugar, granulated sugar and oil for 2 minutes.
Beat in buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, stir in zucchini.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan lightly greased.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Set aside.
Separate biscuits and flatten each on baking pan.
Peel, core and slice apple.
Chop apple in small pieces.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over biscuits.
Top with chopped apples.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Drizzle caramel topping over pecans.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: divinity cake icing
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it will spin a thread.
Beat egg whites stiff while syrup is boiling (not too dry).
Pour 1/2 of syrup over egg whites slowly, beating at 10 to 12 on mixer. Let other half of syrup cook until it bubbles real thick.
Pour this over first part and cream until stiff and cool.
Do not spread on cake until it has cooled or it will be sticky.
If it gets too hard, add little hot water to it or sit pot in hot water. If weather is pretty, add cream of tartar; if not, do not add, then add vanilla.

title: saint paul's pie
directions: Brown beef and sausage in frying pan.
Add onion, pepper and celery.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Bring water to a boil and add rice and soup mix.
Let cool about 7 to 8 minutes.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and set aside to cool completely. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: martinelli
directions: Mix together, then chill.

title: new orleans potato soup
directions: Combine onion, celery and
ham	in saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Simmer until
tender.
Whirl through blender.
Melt margarine and add flour and milk together to make a thin white sauce.
Add potato, onion, celery
and
ham.
Mix white sauce, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: tasty apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar in pan. Cook until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day or 8 hours, mix together apples, nuts, Cool Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and pineapple juice;
mix and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hummus
directions: In bowl of food processor or blender, combine first five ingredients; process until smooth and creamy in texture, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Add salt and pepper.
Taste and add salt, pepper or lemon juice as needed.
If too thick, add small amounts of lemon juice and olive oil.
Transfer to a shallow bowl; sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Eat as dip for pita bread.

title: pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Tear bread into pieces and add onion, water, butter, seasoning.
Mix and place on top of each pork chop.
Mix soup with 1/8 cup water and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into a 9-1/2 x 13 pan, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and peanut butter until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with chocolate chips or chopped nuts, if desired.
Chill 6 hours.

title: emily's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips; add Eagle Brand milk and mix together, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Put wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Pour mixture out and spread with a spoon across the cookie sheet (evenly).
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Cut and enjoy.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir as little as you can.
Put on floured surface.
Knead four times.
Cook at 425°; do not brown.

title: e.s.p. cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies. Add chocolate or butterscotch chips, if desired.

title: heartland tornado
directions: Spoon Cool Whip evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Make a depression in centers, spread up sides of dishes.
Prepare pudding and milk as directed, let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon into hole in Cool Whip.
Swirl like a tornado.
Refrigerate until serving time. Lip smackin' easy.

title: big time potato salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with enough mayonnaise to transform lot into potato salad.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Accept no substitutions.
Must use Best Foods or Hellmann's mayonnaise for super results.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley.
Serves 20 polite company or 7 potato salad lovers.

title: joey's meat loaf
directions: Combine loaf ingredients and cook for 50 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: ed burba's chili(ed's cafe, whitesboro circa 1900-1935)
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix all ingredients and simmer.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and 1 tube of crushed crackers; place in casserole.
Mix 1 tube crackers with melted margarine; sprinkle on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy cherry squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, baking mix and granulated sugar.
Stir in margarine until moistened.
Press in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 9 minutes.

title: forester stew
directions: Cook and simmer.
When serving, sprinkle grated cheese on top. Serve with Fritos.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook sausage over medium heat until lightly browned (10 minutes). Remove from pan and drain all but 3 tablespoons fat from pan. Saute garlic and onion in sausage fat until transparent. Add sausage and cook 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes, breaking apart; add wine, broth, basil, oregano and fennel. Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Skim excess fat from top. Before serving add parsley, green pepper, zucchini and noodles. Simmer for 20 minutes, until noodles are tender. Add salt and pepper as desired. Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top. Serves 6-8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Allow cookie dough to come to room temperature.
Roll out to fit pizza pan (approximately 14-inch size).
Bake according to directions on cookie carton.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip on baked dough.
Add fruit in pattern as desired.
Fresh ones should be tossed in Fruit Fresh.

title: rice vegetable pilaf
directions: In a large pot combine onion and 2 tablespoons chicken broth until onions are tender.
Shred carrot and zucchini.
Add rice, rest of chicken broth, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a rapid boil, stirring occasionally.
Cover, reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes or until moisture is absorbed.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix corn meal and flour in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and egg; beat in mix.
Pour in milk and warm water.
Heat skillet or muffin pan slightly.
Add cooking oil and margarine in warm skillet or muffin pan.
Pour mixture into skillet or pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook cornbread in skillet for 20 to 25 minutes or muffins 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken breasts(for economy, bone the chicken breasts yourself)
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (190° C).
Wash chicken breasts; pat dry with paper towels.
Place chicken breast pieces between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with the flat side of a meat mallet until thin and about doubled in size.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over chicken. In a small bowl, combine butter, oregano and parsley.
Spread 1/2 of butter mixture over 1 side of chicken breasts.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Roll up each chicken breast tightly, tucking in ends to make each stuffed breast the same length as others.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder, beating until well combined.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with pie filling.
Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle 1/2 over pie filling.
Top with remaining batter and then remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: banana creme pie
directions: Roll out dough;
shape in pan and stick with a fork.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Mix cheese and butter, then add flour.
Make about a 2-inch roll and chill.
Slice as thin as possible.
Sprinkle pecans and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven or until edges are lightly browned.

title: lemon parsley marinade
directions: In medium bowl, combine all marinade ingredients.
Use to marinate 2 1/2 to 3 pounds of chicken pieces.
Cook as desired, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cookies may not look done.
Other combinations may be added:
chocolate chips, coconut, nuts, raisins, caramel chips, etc.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise, salts and crabmeat.
Spread on split muffins. Cut muffins into quarters.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bag. Do not thaw when ready to serve.
Place frozen on cookie sheet. Broil until bubbly and crisp.

title: noodles and ham casserole
directions: Cook medium noodles.
Cube cooked ham.
For sauce, warm mushroom soup.
Mix sour cream and finely minced fresh onion (3 to 5 tablespoons).
Layer the noodles, ham and then sauce.
On top, add chow mein noodles or slivered almonds.
Bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: baked ham slices
directions: Mix water and vinegar and bring to a boiling point.
Now mix the brown sugar and the dry mustard together and spread over the ham slice.
Place ham in open baking pan and pour water and vinegar mixture around it.
Do not cover ham with this mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This also gives you a delicious gravy for use over ham when serving.
Serves 4.

title: ladies aid chili
directions: In heavy pot, brown ground beef, onions, peppers and garlic. Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients except beans and corn meal.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add beans and corn meal.
Corn meal serves as a thickener and adds a special flavor. Stir until desired thickness.
Add hot peppers or Tabasco for hot chili.
Recipe can be doubled.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat sour cream and cheese together; add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add chives, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole; dot with additional butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Beat eggs at high speed until light.
Cream shortening 1 minute at high speed.
Continue beating while adding sugar, then beat 1 minute longer to thoroughly mix.
Add beaten eggs and mix 1 minute at medium speed to blend.
Add the dry ingredients and beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in the rest of the dry ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Stir in nuts and beat with spoon.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll in wax paper and store in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 minutes at 400°.

title: white yeast bread
directions: Stir yeast, sugar, salt and 1/3 of flour in a mixing bowl. Heat water, Pet milk and shortening in a saucepan until warm.
Add to flour mixture and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Mix in remaining flour.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Shape into smooth ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Grease dough lightly.
Cover and let rise until dough doubles in size.
Divide into 2 equal parts and shape into loaves. Put in greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender and blend until lemon is pulverized.
Pour contents through a sieve and serve over crushed ice. Yields about 2 cups.

title: wilkes co. barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Use to baste chicken or pork.
Store indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: tuna-egg-cheese overnight casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in skillet and brown ground beef.
Stir in soup mix, beans, catsup, water, mustard and vinegar.
Pour in 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: jello sandwich
directions: Dissolve each package of jello in boiling water in separate bowls.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 6 tablespoons soft oleo.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly until full rolling boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour over warm popcorn. Mix gently to coat with buttered hands to form balls.
"Caution" mix is hot.
Place on wax paper.
To keep popcorn warm set in oven until ready to use.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13 casserole. Bake for 20 minutes.
Stir and continue baking additional 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute meat and next 6 ingredients. Drain grease. Add soup and soy sauce. Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Last, fold in sour cream with meat mixture and pour over noodles.
Top with almonds. Serve as is or bake as casserole at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: frozen coconut cake
directions: Take coconut out of freezer to thaw.
Bake cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven and take a fork and punch holes all over cake while it's still in the pan.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
When this has soaked in (approximately 30 minutes), pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
After this has soaked in (approximately 30 minutes), spread container of Cool Whip over top of cake.
Sprinkle with entire package of thawed coconut. Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours or until chilled. Refrigerate after serving.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs with water and milk mixture.
Stir in sifted flour and salt.
Beat excessively.
Pour drippings from roast beef into 8 or 9-inch pan, greased.
Put pan into 450° oven until fat begins to smoke.
Pour in batter and bake for 20 to 30 minutes until puffed and brown.
Serve with gravy.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix in refried beans and 1/4 to 1/2 cup salsa.
Simmer until hot.
Roll mixture into tortillas and place filled tortillas in a baking dish.
Top with sour cream, shredded cheese and remaining salsa in that order.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dressing and corn chips. Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Add dressing and chips.
Toss and serve.
This can be made the day before, then add dressing and chips a few minutes before serving.

title: kellogg's rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until coated with marshmallow mixture.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Toss flour, bran, salt, soda and nutmeg together with fork. Stir in orange rind, apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour the juice of 1 orange into a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add buttermilk to make 2 cups.
Add egg, molasses and oil; stir.
Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Pour into greased muffin tins, 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: listhe(cookie)
directions: Mix ingredients until dough is consistency of pie crust dough. Handle as little as possible.
Cut dough in half and roll to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes (not too small) and slit centers and sides with a knife to keep from filling up with air. Fry in deep hot lard until lightly browned on each side.
Drain on paper towel until cooled.
Dust with powdered sugar just before serving.
Very fattening, but very good; was given to me by my great aunt, Helen Smith.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, sugar and mashed bananas together; blend well.
Add dry ingredients, milk, vinegar and brandy.
Mix together flour, nuts and raisins and fold into batter.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese and green chili rice
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Cool and mix with sour cream.
In buttered casserole, put layer of rice/cream mixture, about 1/3 of total. Add layer of 1/3 of cheese, 1/3 of chilies.
Repeat twice ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip coconut squares
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs into butter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Sprinkle coconut. Top with sweetened condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, cut into squares.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Heat chicken stock.
Add celery and carrots.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Set aside.
Heat butter in a saucepan. Add the onions and saute lightly.
Add the flour and stir with a wire whisk.
Cook for 2 to 4 minutes, making sure flour and butter are well blended.
Add vegetable broth and milk.
Stir with a wire whisk; bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low as it thickens.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve. Garnish with chopped fresh parsley or bacon bits.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Will rise and fill pan only to fall flat later, hence the name.
Cut in squares.

title: texas trash
directions: Place margarine in a microwave-safe casserole.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add pretzel bits and cereals.
Mix well. Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir at 3 minutes.
Add nuts and mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Can put in round bottom bowl.
Chill overnight.
Use spatula around edges and turn out onto platter. Pat with chipped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: almond christmas bars
directions: Cream butter with sugar until it's very fluffy.
Add sugar, flour, almonds and vanilla.
Mix well.
Take a teaspoonful of dough.
Roll it between hands until it starts to form a ball.
Push in a cherry with thumb and finish rolling to make a perfect ball. Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 35 minutes at 325°.
While still hot, roll in sugar to coat.
Cool on racks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until thoroughly cooked, then pull meat from bones and tear into generous pieces.
Combine cream of chicken soup and milk in pan and stir until it has a smooth consistency.
Then put pieces of chicken and vegetables in with the soup and heat thoroughly.
Place in a casserole dish.
Roll out crescent rolls and place on top.
Bake at 350° until rolls are done.

title: microwave stir-fry
directions: Cut
steak
across
grain.
Set aside.	Place mushrooms and next 4 ingredients in 2 quart casserole.
Cover dish with wax paper.
Microwave
on
High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Stir once. Drain
well.
Stir in meat.
Cover.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4
1/2 minutes.
Stir twice.
Meat will be pink.
Blend cornstarch
into soy sauce.	Combine with gravy and ginger.	Stir in
meat mixture.
Cover;
microwave on High, 4 to 6 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: Saute onion in oil in large pan for 3 minutes.
Add water, salt and bouillon.
Heat to boiling.
Gradually add noodles. Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve.
(Quick, easy and delicious!)

title: cheddar cheese pumpkin(autumn appetizer)
directions: Mix in medium bowl the Cheddar cheese and cream cheese, until well blended.
Stir in peanuts, carrots, onion and dill. Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour. Shape into pumpkin or ball shape.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads; add other ingredients except margarine. Mix well. Pour into crock-pot. Dot with margarine. Cover and cook on low 4 hours.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: taco casserole
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Combine enchilada and tomato sauces.
Stir together 2 cups sauce, coffee and meat mixture.
Set aside.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix whipped cream, yogurt and amount desired of dry jello.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
You can mix with washed and cut fruit for a fruit salad or use as a dip.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low overnight (approximately 12 hours).
You may add vegetables.
If added, also add a 2nd can of mushroom soup.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Mix together and pour the oil, dressing mix, salt and pepper over pretzels in a large roaster. Bake in a 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: no syrup pecan pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: shell pasta and crabs
directions: In a large saucepan, mix tomato paste (2 cans water and 1
can paste) and dry spice ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat. If fresh, clean crab bodies, removing outside shell and
feelers. Remove
pinchers
and reserve in freezer.
Wash crab
bodies
well and put in tomato sauce.
Bring to boil and simmer for at least 45 minutes.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate beef or venison 8 hours or overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a deep, 2-quart casserole, combine butter and onion. Microwave on High 2 minutes to tender.
Stir in flour, celery salt and pepper.
Microwave 30 seconds.
Stir in milk; microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir 3 times.
Stir in cheese; microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir twice.
Stir in macaroni and pimento.
Cover and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in parsley. Top with tomato slices and pepper rings.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Microwave at full power (High) 2 minutes or until pepper and tomato are heated through.

title: caramel-no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil in large pan the sugar, butter and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add instant pudding; mix well.
Add oats and mix thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls and let set.
Good as candy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 9 x 13 baking dish; mix chili, enchilada sauce, half of corn chips and one cup of cheese. Top with rest of chips and cheese, bake until cheese is melted.

title: mama's coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oil, sugar and salt; remove 3/4 cup of this mixture and put aside for topping. Mix well together the egg, buttermilk, nutmeg, baking powder and soda. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: winter bean soup
directions: Wash beans well and cover with 6 to 8 cups hot water; bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour. Drain.
Add 2 quarts cold water and ham bone.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the remaining ingredients and let simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: pop pop kelly's old fashioned potato salad(30 or 40 servings)
directions: Stir all ingredients together to mix.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, into cream cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise and onions.
Stir in crabmeat (chopped finely) and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Makes about 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: chop suey
directions: Heat shortening.
Cook meat for 2 minutes on high heat, stirring.

Add soy sauce, celery (all the leaves chopped from the top) and 4 or 5 outside stalks, sliced; mushrooms, bean sprouts and onion sliced crosswise 3 times then finely sliced up and down. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes with lid on, stirring often.

title: dole ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Use juice as a beverage. Combine pineapple, oranges, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and almonds.
Fold in yogurt.
Chill.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using 1 1/3 cups Coca-Cola in place of water and stirring 1 tablespoon grated orange peel into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert cake onto wire rack; cool completely.
(Cake may be made and stored, tightly wrapped up to 2 days before decorating.)

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add in kidney beans (do not drain).
Add onion.
Add chili powder (more if desired).
If you want it hot, add in crushed red pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, shortening and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press half in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Pour in rhubarb.
Combine white sugar, water, vanilla and cornstarch and cook until clear and thick.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and hot water over low heat; cool.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt, butter and buttermilk.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat one minute at medium speed (scraping bowl).
Add eggs, melted chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Beat one minute at medium speed.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch pans.

title: cottage cheese pineapple salad
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O, lime Jell-O, hot water, pineapple and lemon juice, if desired, in large bowl. In another bowl, mix cottage cheese, milk, salad dressing and nutmeats (optional). Combine and chill.

title: yam bake
directions: Slice yams and arrange into layers with pineapple in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil rapidly for 3 minutes.
Pour over yams and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and corn oil well.
Add flour, soda, salt, apples, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Grease tube pan well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and flour. Then add melted margarine and mix well. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° until custard is set.

title: no name cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and pour in pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes in a tube cake pan.

title: tabbouleh (a salad)(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Wash bulgar.
Cover with hot water and allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and then squeeze dry with hands.
Chop the vegetables and mix together.
Beat in oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix with bulgar until well blended, then chill.

title: kool-aid mix
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 1/2 teaspoon or more as desired of the mix per one cup of water.
The mixture can be sealed in a plastic bag for travel or camping.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of sliced potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Repeat until casserole is full.
Pour milk over, barely covering potatoes.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with additional butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together all but chocolate chips and press in 13 x 9 pan. Melt chocolate chips and pour over top. Let set and cut in squares.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that is floured and greased.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in bite size pieces; fry and drain.
Fry beef and drain.
Saute onion.
Add ketchup, mustard and sugar and stir together.
Add beans and heat.

title: chocolate chip pralines
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture, along with chocolate chips.
Mix together and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Flatten out dough.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Check cookies; bake 1 more minute, if needed.
Do not overbake as the edges will get too hard.

title: lucille's cherry nut salad
directions: Heat cherries and pineapple juice to boiling.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: hobo meal(serves 3 to 4)
directions: On a square of aluminum foil, place in center a large hamburger of the ground beef. On this place a slice of onion, 4 to 6 pieces of potato, 4 to 6 pieces of carrot and 2 pieces celery. Dot veggies with butter. Season with salt and pepper. Wrap. Place on baking tray and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes. Loosen foil and brown if desired. May also use chicken, pork chop or round steak for ground meat.

title: tofu pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Osterize tofu and jello mix on low speed.
Pour mixture into pie shell; chill in refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip and serve.
Garnish with fresh fruit (strawberry, peach, lime, orange).

title: caramel icebox pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust; chill.
Pour caramel topping on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: special spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze dry spinach.
In a medium bowl, blend vegetable recipe soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir in spinach and water chestnuts; chill.
Makes about 3 cups dip.

title: avys' lace cornbread
directions: Add water to make thin consistency.
Blend all ingredients in a blender.
On a hot greased griddle, fry 4 inch patties to a golden brown, turning once.
The thinner the consistency, the more "lace" you get.

title: cathy's baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place face up in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place pat of butter in center of each apple.
Prepare sauce.
Cook sauce over low heat 5 minutes.
Pour over apples and bake until tender at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm topped with walnut pieces.
Great by itself or served with vanilla ice cream.

title: 30-day cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans (Bundt, 9 x 13-inch or 6 loaf pans) that will all fit in oven at the same time.
Drain fruit into large bowl.
Pour juice into 3 pint jars. These are new starter for friends.
(Cake should be started within 5 days after receiving starter.)

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans. Boil together vinegar, brown sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour this over the beans and add other vegetables.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder together.
Add sugar, eggs and oil and beat together with mixer for one minute.
Add pineapple, coconut, carrots and walnuts and mix everything together.
Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam and then add batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with butter and lemon juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into casserole dish, place under broiler until browned.
Add soup diluted with water.
Add mushrooms and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Blend other ingredients.
Pour in loaf
pan
and
bake
at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick tested comes out clean.

title: ore-ida hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, onion and cheese in large casserole dish.
Melt butter, crackers (crumbled) and stuffing mix together and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashion chocolate cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add flour and milk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 round cake pans.

title: apple-chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on bed of lettuce. Serves 4.

title: mom's holiday cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Add eggs and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla, soda, baking powder, nutmeg and flour.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, dates, coconut and nuts.
Mix well and chill for one hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked boston brown bread
directions: Butter two No. 2 cans. Mix sugar, raisins, soda and salt. Add butter and pour water over all. Simmer for 5 minutes and cool. Add egg and flour to mixture. Blend. Pour into cans. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix soda, baking powder and salt with flour.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately with sour cream, walnuts and other mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour into three 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: simple bundt cake
directions: Mix 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Place on rack.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 dish with Pam. Wash potatoes and bake in oven like you would do a normal baked potato. Cut half of the potatoes up into chunks and place in dish. Top with sour cream and cheese. Cut other half of potatoes up into chunks and place in dish. Top with other half of sour cream and cheese. Top with crumbled bacon and onions. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted.

title: mexican omelets
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Add sausage, ham, bell pepper and tomatoes; cook until done.
Add garlic powder, ground comino, black pepper, dried onion and fresh green onions.
Add 1 1/2 cups of Hot Sauce (recipe follows), chorizos and potatoes.
Simmer all until cooked.
Add 1 1/2 cups of grated cheese.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat until it looks like cake batter. Add milk and vanilla to mixture to fill mixing bowl.
Pour mixture into freezer; add remaining milk.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: mozzarella cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix eggs, cream and half the cheese together.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is raised.
The cheese will flatten, if not served promptly.

title: deer pepperoni
directions: Mix in bowl.
Roll on wax paper in 2-inch long rolls. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza dough for stromboli
directions: In large mixing bowl, mound flour and make a well in the middle.
Pour yeast in that well.
Add just a little water to that yeast and start stirring.
As it gathers flour and a paste starts to form, add more water.
Do this until all water is used up. Knead dough about 15 minutes.
Place a teaspoon of oil in bowl and coat dough with it.
Cover well with plastic wrap.
Place in warm place and let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Roll into 8-inch circles.
Put in filling.
Fold in half and seal.
Brush top of stromboli with oil.
On lightly oiled cookie sheets, bake in preheated 450° oven for 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients
together and bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes in a 6 x 9-inch pan.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar flour and salt; set aside.
In saucepan, mix margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and then pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is creamy.
Pour mixture on cookie sheet (make sure cookie sheet has sides) that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon.
Add to mixture in small amounts until thoroughly mixed.
Add vanilla and other ingredients.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: collector's item cornbread stuffing
directions: This mixture will be wet and thin.
It becomes light and fluffy while baking at 350° until set and brown as desired.

title: yellow squash fritters
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir eggs into squash mixture, then add butter. Drop fritter batter by tablespoons onto greased griddle.
Cook until light brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in top of large double boiler set over simmering (not boiling) water on low heat.
Beat with electric hand mixer 5 to 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove and continue beating until frosting is smooth and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In mixing bowl, mix soup, onion, mayonnaise and egg.
Layer casserole dish with half of broccoli, layer of cheese and 1/2 sauce.
Repeat process.
Top with dressing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving the 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix all ingredients in a loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: refreshing fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off fruits to even 3 cups; may need to add 1 to 1 1/4 cups of water to even the 3 cups.
Put fruits in a bowl and set in refrigerator.
Pour into small saucepan; bring to a boil, reduce heat and add packages of pudding.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour into a medium size dish or bowl.
Set in refrigerator until cool.
Stir in pineapple, oranges and slices bananas (best to add bananas the day you are serving the fruit salad).
Top with maraschino cherries.
Enjoy!
Great for any occasion.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well. Chill well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Break up cauliflower serving size.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread Miracle Whip light like frosting to cover and leave to set.
When ready to serve, mix dressing and cheese all through salad.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Melt oleo, add marshmallows and salt.
Add dry jello and stir. Pour over 3-quarts popped corn.
Stir.
Grease hands and form into 15 balls.
Any color jello may be used.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Melt 12 ounce package chocolate chips and 1/2 cake paraffin.
Place ball on toothpick, immerse in melted chocolate, leaving small area to make it look like a buckeye.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Cook over low heat and beat until lukewarm.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Mix (high speed) until fluffy.
Refrigerate several hours before using.
Yields 1 quart.

title: lemon squares
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: american indian corn pudding
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Preheat oven to 350°. Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour quickly over medium heat; heat until smooth paste forms.
Stir paste constantly while adding milk and allow the mixture to boil.
Lower heat; add egg yolks, salt and pepper and corn.
Mix; turn off heat.
Fold in egg whites with rubber spatula.
Pour in dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chocolate peanut-marshmallow candy
directions: Melt almond bark in the microwave or in a large saucepan.
Add enough peanuts and marshmallows to take up liquid.
Stir until well coated.
Pour out on cookie sheet that has been lined with wax paper.
Place in freezer until set, about 10 minutes.
Break or cut into bite size pieces.
This is very fast and easy.
With adult supervision, children can make this.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients.
Add jello.
Chill to soft set.
Whip milk until it stands in peaks and fold into other mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: stollen
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in 2 cups flour, yeast, eggs, cardamon and fruit.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface.
Place dough in greased bowl; grease top of dough down.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add honey, sugar, salt, other spices and flaked coconut in a large bowl.
Add sweet potatoes and cream; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix butter, graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, confectioners sugar, vanilla and peanut butter in a large bowl. Lay foil on the table and roll small size balls out on it.
In a double boiler, melt semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin, when melted dip balls into mixture and place on foil to cool.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, vanilla, eggs and butter well, then add flour and mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Dump all ingredients into ovenproof casserole bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; beat with wooden spoon. Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish. Chill.

title: orange juice cooler
directions: Blend juice, club soda and crushed ice in blender until frothy.
Garnish with strawberries or fresh mint sprigs.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
