Mix together in a shallow bowl or pan: milk, eggs, nutmeg and salt.
In another bowl mix together Ricotta and cream cheese.
Slice bread into thick slices and generously spread the cheese mixture on one side of each piece.
Spread jam on every other piece of bread on top of the cheese mix.
Mash together 2 pieces (mix side in) to form a sandwich.
Dip (not soak) each sandwich in egg mixture and brown 3 to 4 minutes on each side in very hot canola oil.
Place each browned sandwich on a baking pan and bake for 25 minutes in the oven (they will puff up).
Serve with butter, jam or syrup.

title: layered salad
directions: Put lettuce in bottom of bowl or 13 x 9 x 2 glass pan.
Add in layers, celery, peppers, onions, and peas.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar
and spoon over top sealing the edges with mayo mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix together, with hands, all ingredients, roll into balls and bake on cookie sheet (ungreased) for 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: bishops chocolate pie
directions: Mix cookies (crushed) and margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Combine dry puddings in large bowl.
Add milk and mix as directed.
Add ice cream.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate curls.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all and put in ice cream freezer.

title: sweet and sour
directions: Cube prime roll and brown in deep fat.
Saute pepper, celery and onion.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar; add the lemon and pineapple juices.
Combine all ingredients except prime roll. Cook until thickened.
Pour over prime roll and simmer 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Spread 3/4 of cheese and spinach on the bottom of pie shell. Beat the cream, eggs and salt together until frothy.
Pour over cheese and spinach.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pie is set. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9-inch graham crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: brother john's beef stew
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, cook onions, stirring often, until lightly browned, about 10 minutes; with slotted spoon remove to bowl.
In a large bowl, toss beef with flour, salt, and pepper. In the same Dutch oven, over high heat in 2 tablespoons hot oil, cook beef, half at a time, until well browned on all sides.
With slotted spoon, remove beef to another bowl as it browns.

title: nut fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil, then boil 4 1/2 minutes over medium heat.
Add to mixture of chocolate bars, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Whip, salt, vanilla and nut meats.
Pour out into buttered pans.
Set in refrigerator 3 hours before cutting.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: quick cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into slices.
Boil in salt water for 10 minutes. Drain carefully twice in cold water.
Mix soup, milk and add to cabbage.
Shred cheese and put over top.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: steak kabobs
directions: Mix tomato juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Place meat in shallow glass dish; pour tomato juice mixture over meat.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove meat from marinade; reserve marinade. On 6 skewers, alternate meat, vegetables and pineapple.
Place on grill 4 inches from coals.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade.
Makes 6 servings.

title: irish potato candy]
directions: Mash potato and combine thoroughly with sugar and vanilla. (If mixture is too stiff, add one teaspoon milk.)
Roll out on lightly floured board surface.
Spread peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut in circles.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Cook chicken in skillet about 10 minutes. Mix cream of broccoli soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Slice thin slices lemon and put a piece on each piece of chicken.
Cover and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook on medium-low heat.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Make up dumplings and drop in vinegar mixture.

title: lemon and blueberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange in a 2-quart bowl.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions; pour over pound cake.
Spoon blueberry pie filling over the pudding, then spread whipped topping over the blueberry pie filling. Chill.
If you wish, you may top with toasted almonds.

title: bethany's favorite fruit slush
directions: Heat sugar and water or fruit juices until dissolved.
Add lemonade, orange juice and fruits.
Mix and freeze

title: meat loaf - hunt's style(with sweet sour sauce)
directions: Mix ingredients and form one large or two small loaves. Bake in shallow baking dish (approximately 1 1/2-inches deep) in 350° oven.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together. Add the remaining ingredients to taste. Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese; mix in sugar and salad dressing.
Add fruit and nuts; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 10 x 5-inch pan, or individual servers.
Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix margarine
with
1	cup
sugar until blended.
Then beat eggs in,
one
at a time.
Stir flour with baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.	Blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in sour cream.
Pour
batter
in
greased
and
flour-dusted
9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter chocolate chips and nuts over batter and sprinkle with
remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Do not refrigerate.

title: jello casserole
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Add pineapple to Jell-O.
Mix 1 cup of pineapple juice, sugar, egg and flour and cook until thick.
Pour on top of Jell-O.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put on top of pineapple sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter and place in deep roasting pan. Add rice and soups.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Onion and/or celery can be added for flavor.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Spread in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour caramel topping on top of cheese mixture. Cover caramel with chopped nuts.
Serve with apple slices.

title: boiled cake(ciste beirithe)
directions: Put water in saucepan. Add butter, sugar and fruit. Boil for 3 minutes. Allow to cool slighlty.
Place flour, salt, almonds (chopped) and remainder of ingredients in mixing bowl. Add cooled ingredients and whipped eggs to mixture in bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Place in a 9-inch tin. Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Mix milk with cheesecake mix and beat for 3 minutes.
Add morsels to mix, then add raisins to mix.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in seasoned, boiling water.
Cool, debone and chop into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Smash Doritos chips in the bag and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream, soups, chilies and milk.
Mix well by hand.
In a large, deep casserole layer chips, chicken, sauce and cheese, beginning with chips and ending with chips and cheese.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Delicious and easy.

title: oysters in bacon
directions: Cut Bacon Strips into 4 inch lengths.
Wash oysters in their own liquid; and place one on each strip of bacon.
Squeeze a little lemon juice over them, then add a dash of cayenne pepper.
Roll up each one in their strip of bacon and fasten with a skewer.	Put them in a hot oven of 415° and cook for 8 to 10 minute.
To serve, replace in warmed shells and add a dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: sweet-and-sour pork
directions: Cut the tenderloin into 1 1/2 x 1/4-inch strips; set aside. Drain pineapple, reserving juice in a small bowl.
Set pineapple aside.
To juice, add ketchup, water, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and ginger; stir until smooth.

title: crazy crust beef pie
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch glass pie pan.
Combine flour, shortening, buttermilk and egg in medium mixing bowl.
Stir until blended (batter will be lumpy).
Spread batter thinly on bottom of pan and thickly up sides to within 1/4-inch of rim.
Fill and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: zucchini tomato bake
directions: In colander, combine zucchini and salt.
Let drain for 30 minutes.
Squeeze out excess moisture in clean towel.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine zucchini, tomatoes, onion, Swiss cheese, sour cream and pepper.
Mix well and put in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan and boil until thick enough to spread.
Mixture must be stirred constantly while cooking.
When ready, mixture will splatter and pop.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yields about 5 pints.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick and yeast in a bowl.
Add sugar and water and mix well.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Knead on a floured surface, then roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and place on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Brush top of rolls with melted margarine.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.
Serve with egg sauce.

title: "golden glow" mock-tail
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and simmer over medium-low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove spices and serve.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple; add sour cream, marshmallows, nuts and cherries.
Mix and place in refrigerator until cool.

title: club cracker bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with Club crackers.
Cook crushed graham crackers, margarine, milk, brown sugar and white sugar for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Cool a bit and pour over Club crackers in pan.
Then top with another layer of Club crackers.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter and pour over for frosting. Best if kept in refrigerator.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot dill
directions: Let come to boil and boil 10 minutes.
Pack clean jars with cucumbers and add 2 cloves garlic, 3 hot peppers, 1 dill head, pour hot liquid in jar leaving 1/2-inch of space in top.
Seal at once with hot lid.
When pickles are ready to eat take out of jar, cut in 4 lengths wise pieces, return to jar and let sit in refrigerator for 3 days then they are ready to eat.

title: grilled steak with wine sauce
directions: Brush steak on both sides with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes on each side or to desired taste. Place on heated serving platter; cover loosely with foil.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Slice across grain.

title: divinity
directions: Watch carefully during last stage of cooking for temperature will rise rapidly.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan. Cook until bubbly. Stir constantly and cook 6 minutes. Timing is important. Remove from heat and add chips, butter, nuts and vanilla. Stir only until butter and chips are melted.

title: pecan clusters*
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except pecans.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed.
Stir in pecans.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls, 1/2-inch apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks; cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: velveeta cheese salsa dip
directions: Cut the cheese into cubes and place in a 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Add milk and microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir mixture, then heat again until cheese melts.
Add the tomatoes; stir well and heat about 3 minutes or until hot.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken and dressing with gravy
directions: *You may also use a 3 or 4 lb. package of cut up chicken.

title: marta's oatmeal patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop from a spoon into hot oil (just enough oil to cover bottom of pan).
Brown nicely on both sides. Serve hot.

title: apple pie
directions: In saucepan, add sugar and juice; bring to a boil. Add apples; simmer, uncovered, until clear and tender. Do not boil. Take out apples and cool. Make paste of cornstarch, water and salt. Add to syrup; cook until it thickens. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter. Put apples into unbaked pie crust. Pour juice over and make a crisscross pie crust top. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture.
Roll in balls the size of a teaspoon; dip in sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet, 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add onion and garlic.
Add vinegar and oil, beating well.
Store in refrigerator.
This salad dressing was used at the County Fair for many years.

title: cheesy taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Place broken chips into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add taco seasoning to drained beef and cook as package says.
Add water and simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add refried beans, mushrooms and olives and simmer 5 more minutes. Put meat mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese is melted, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and taco sauce.
If you are not going to bake right away, keep mixture hot in the crock-pot so it doesn't dry out.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. To make crumb mixture for bottom crust and topping, cream the butter with brown sugar until fluffy.
Cut in flour and nuts. Reserve 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of prepared pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: becky's cheese casserole loaf
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Let mixture stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Add to mixture the cheese and flour.
Blend well.
Cover with Saran or towel and let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Stir batter down and beat 1/2 minute.

title: one dish meat dinner
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper and drain.
Add tomatoes, syrup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook shell macaroni and drain.
Mix with meat sauce and put in large casserole.
Top with 1 cup sharp cheese (grated).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked cornish hens
directions: Mix oil and spices, rub on hens.
Place skin side up on lightly greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.
Per serving, has 228 calories, 23 grams protein, 0 carbohydrates, 15 grams fat and 73 mg.
cholesterol.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package. Drain well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, mustard and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly. Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: parm-a-chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, flour, paprika and pepper. Dip chicken in egg and milk.
Combine flour, cheese and coat chicken.
Place in greased pan and pour melted margarine over chicken.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: spicy raisin sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water; cook about 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook until jelly melts and is well heated.
Good with ham.
Enjoy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add taco seasoning to meat and stir well.
Combine soups, tomatoes and 1 can water; heat until well blended.
Layer meat, chips and half of soup mixture; top with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix, milk, eggs and onion. Spread in greased baking dish (12 x 7-inch).
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Spoon over the top of the batter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand five minutes before cutting.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in flat casserole dish.

title: low-fat white sauce
directions: Cook evaporated milk until hot.
Add flour.
Cook over medium heat until desired consistency.
Add garlic, basil and pepper to taste.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Season with sugar, seasoned pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix well and enjoy on crispy lettuce leaf.

title: chinese beets
directions: Drain beet juice. Set aside. In saucepan, mix sugar, flour, cloves, salt, vanilla, ketchup and vinegar. Add beet juice. Cook until thick. Add onions. Cut beets into bite size. Add to mixture. Cook over medium heat approximately 3 or 4 minutes. Chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions in olive oil.
Drain.
Add butter, salts and garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours, covered,in a large pot or Dutch oven, over low heat.

title: base for cream soup
directions: Saute all vegetables in butter.
Then add flour and also chicken stock.
Bring to a boil. Heat cream carefully and add to stock.
Use your own choice of vegetables for the cream soup (broccoli, cauliflower, potatoes, etc.).

title: sunday casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.
Fix before church and it will be ready for lunch when you get home!

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften. Mix cream cheese, green onions, olives, mushrooms, dried beef and Accent together.
Chill, then form into 2 to 3 balls.
Roll in bacon bits.
Serve with Wheat Thin crackers.

title: jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Cut off top 1/4 of oranges.
With serrated grapefruit knife, free the whole orange from its rind.
Be careful not to pierce skin.
Reserve oranges for grilling.

title: irene's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk; stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples evenly over the dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger with pepper and onion.
Drain fat when cooked thoroughly.
Add a can of B & M baked beans, ketchup and 6 tablespoons crushed hot peppers.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring constantly.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Blend all ingredients and store in tightly covered container. Use 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup boiling water per cup.

title: party mix for kids of all ages
directions: Mix honey, oil, vanilla and peanut butter.
Heat only until combined.
Pour over cereal and spread over a cookie sheet. Bake at 225 degrees for 1 hour, stirring frequently. Remove and cool completely.
Add M&M's, Reeses pieces and raisins.
Store in airtight containers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into crust and bake.

title: crab salad
directions: Break up crab in bite sizes.
Chop up celery and onions (small).
Chop up black olives; add cheese.
Blend to taste with Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers and enjoy.

title: darling cake
directions: Mix sugar, lard, oatmeal and flour well.
Add water and soda and add to mixture.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Spread 3/4 mixture in pan. Boil dates or raisins with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Top with salted peanuts and remaining dough.
Bake at 350° until done (35 to 50 minutes).

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil to 290° (use candy thermometer).
Pour over 6 quarts of popcorn.
Stir until coated; spread thin on table top to cool.
So easy and so good!

title: corn-corn bread
directions: Mix all until just blended.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: bertha myrtle brooks austin's favorite carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Add oil, eggs and carrots.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Make sure pans are greased and floured.
Can be baked in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm in the center.

title: micro-oven browned potatoes
directions: Heat water, margarine and bouillon together for 1 minute on High.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook, covered, for 6 minutes on full power.
Stir; cook an additional 4 minutes on High and stir again. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: heavenly bars (chess squares)
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and pat in bottom of lightly greased pan.
Beat together last 3 ingredients and pour over other mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes for metal pan, or 350° 40 minutes for glass pan.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put sausage and cheese in a greased 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish. Add seasoning.
Mix together Bisquick mix, milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serving Size: 6 to 8.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Put can of chow mein noodles on top.
Bake a few minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put peeled and cored apples in 2-quart baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut butter into dry ingredients with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° until apples are tender and top is brown.

title: cookout salad
directions: Chop up all vegetables and mix and toss together in large bowl.
Add dressing of your choice and enjoy!

title: joan's applesauce cake
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the shortening, water, nuts, raisins and applesauce and beat for 2 minutes.
Add the egg and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x13 pan and bake for 50 - 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 hour or at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Heat until mixture loses gloss.
Add pecans and drop onto waxed paper.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions (green parts too) and dried beef very fine. Mix altogether.
Shape into a ball.
Serve on crackers.

title: country cabbage and sausage
directions: Wash cabbage and cut into eight sections.
Put cabbage in a pot, add enough water to cover cabbage.
Cook it until tender. Add salt, sugar and grease.
Boil hard for
5 to 10 minutes. Reduce heat and simmer until liquid is low.
Add sausage that has been cut into 3-inch pieces and cook 5 to 10 minutes on medium heat.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook and drain ground beef with onions.
Stir in tomatoes, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; cut and spread flat.
Make dressing. Crush crackers; add bread crumbs.
Melt margarine; mix with the crackers and bread crumbs.
Add seasonings.
Lay shrimp on foil lined cookie sheet.
Place plenty of dressing down center. Preheat oven to 450°, then broil 1 side for 5 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with flour.
Add sausage and water.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all three ingredients together.
Serve with fruit.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter into crust.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg white, 3 teaspoons soy sauce and cornstarch and mix well.
Add chicken; stir to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
In large skillet, over high heat, brown chicken in oil; remove.
Add mushrooms; cook and stir until tender.
Add chicken, broccoli and remaining ingredients except rice; heat thoroughly. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Chop dates.
Put all ingredients into a 2-quart pan.
Stir over heat until blended.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Dip small portion at a time. Roll into ball, then roll in the coconut.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters, then slice by quarters.
Fry cabbage in shortening and butter until almost done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add approximately 1/3 cup water (depending on size of cabbage head).
Simmer about 5 more minutes.
Before removing cabbage, add 2 to 4 tablespoons sugar over top.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Sure is good with good mashed potatoes.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Yields 24 pancakes.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs.
Stir together the flour, soda, spices and salt; add to creamed mixture. Beat together.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 25 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Ladle into 2 pint jars.
Seal and water bath for 10 minutes or keep in refrigerator.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until soft. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Must be kept in freezer or refrigerator. Will not keep on shelf.

title: t - cakes
directions: Combine 1 cup of room temperature butter or shortening with 2 cups sugar and 2 whole eggs.
Beat with blending fork or spoon until well mixed.
Then stir in sifted flour with baking powder. Add vanilla.
Roll very thin and bake quickly in a 425° oven.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Brown the ground beef.
Set aside to cool.
Sift all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add liquids and mix well together, then add cooked ground beef.
Bake in a well greased 9 X 13 inch pan for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add to ground chuck, tomatoes, tomato sauce and eggs.
Mix altogether well.
Add crumbled crackers.
To make ingredients, stick together.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Add catsup to top and I add about 1/2 cup water poured over.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Soften margarine in microwave in large microwave bowl.
Combine all ingredients with margarine. Cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Turn out into pan. Refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil and cook chicken and onion over medium heat until the chicken is no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Add salt, pepper, Italian seasonings, garlic powder, tomato paste, water and mushrooms. Stir well, bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: steamed yellow squash and zucchini
directions: Wash and cut squash and zucchini in slices.
Put in pot with butter and small amount of water.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer until tender.

title: mrs. butterworth's pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the above and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Yield:
2 (9-inch) pies.

title: butter pecan cool whip dessert
directions: Mix and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.
Cool completely.
This can be done a day or so ahead.

title: charlotte's web cake
directions: Frost cake with blue frosting.
Using tube of white decorator frosting, pipe 4 concentric circles, about 1 inch apart and a dot in the center of the cake.
Using spatula or tip of knife, draw through circles at regular intervals, alternating direction each time.
Place jelly beans for spider's body and head on cake.
Cut 8 licorice whip pieces; curve and arrange for legs.

title: grandma jessie's banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and pour into a loaf pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl. Shape into small (ping-pong ball size) balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk fudge cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl; beat at medium speed.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Blend in hot water last.
Put in 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in oven at 350° until they test done.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, oil, salt and baking powder together.
Add the eggs one at a time.
Mix milk, flour, lemon, vanilla and sour cream together and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Freezes well.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly oiled baking sheet (Pam).
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until browned.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add onions.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite barbecue beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Soak overnight in cold soda water. (Add 1 to 2 tablespoons baking soda to water to help "de-gas" them.)
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Cover with water, add ham hocks and simmer gently for 2 hours.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Split bell peppers in half; remove inside, wash, cover with water and boil until tender.

title: baked pork tenderloin(by 7 - 12 year olds)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place tenderloins on rack in roasting pan. Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Spoon about half of the sauce over the loins.
Bake the tenderloins 1 hour and 30 minutes. Heat remaining sauce in saucepan over low heat.
Slice the tenderloins into 1/4 inch diagonal slices on cutting board.
Serve the tenderloins with the remaining sauce.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend the shredded cheese and the soft butter in a mixing bowl.
Sift the flour, salt and paprika.
Mix to form a dough. Shape dough around medium stuffed olives, using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each olive.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
May refrigerate or freeze before baking.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Break up candy in small pieces and put in large dish with jello.
Add boiling water and stir until candy is nearly dissolved.
Add pineapple and juice.
Chill until set, then fold Cool Whip into jello mixture.
Chill.

title: good rich dirt
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together well, then mix the pudding and milk together.
Combine both mixtures, then add the Cool Whip. Crush a large bag of Oreos.
Layer in one large or 2 medium flowerpots.
Cover holes in bottom of pot(s) with waxed paper or foil.
(I use plastic sand buckets.)
Put in a layer of cookies, then pudding, cookies, then pudding.
Finish with cookies on top. Plant artificial flowers before serving.
You can also add gummy worms.

title: lemon nut fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, fruit and nuts.
Add to first mixture.
Add lemon extract. Pour into a greased and floured large tube pan and bake at 275° for 2 hours.
This cake must bake slow, check your oven.

title: bacon cheese biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix and milk.
Fold in bacon and cheese.
Roll and cut biscuits, baking them at 400° to 450° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown on top.
Yields approximately 18 biscuits.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and mix together in baking dish.
Melt sugar, butter and curry powder and pour over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for one hour.

title: peach butter
directions: Mix peaches, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Boil fast on medium-high.
As butter thickens, lower heat.
Add spices and cook until thick enough to almost flake off spoon.
Pour into sterile jars 1/2-inch from top.
Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.

title: chip dip
directions: Place onion soup mix in hot water and let soak for a few minutes.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth with electric mixer or put in food processor.
When creamy, add sour cream.
Mix and serve.

title: cheese snaps
directions: Mix with hand like biscuits.
Roll in a marble size ball. Press with fork and cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well, then add milk and mix.
Break bread into pieces.
Peel apples, core and cut into chunks.
Add all together; sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: italian style pasta salad
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Set aside.
Coarsely chop artichoke hearts. Halve zucchini slices.
In large bowl, combine spaghetti, artichokes, zucchini, carrot, salami and cheeses.
In jar with tight fitting lid, combine dressing, oregano, basil, mustard and garlic; shake well.
Pour dressing over spaghetti mixture.
Toss to coat evenly.
Cover and chill several hours before serving. Makes 8 to 10 side dish servings or 4 to 5 main dish servings.

title: sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered container and refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve and enjoy!

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in Crisco. Add onions, tomatoes, ketchup and steak sauce and simmer for 30 minutes. Add cooked macaroni. Put in a casserole dish. Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sweet sliced pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick.
Mix ingredients together and put into microwave for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: french bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir to blend.
Add shortening.
Pour in tap water.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add 1 cup flour and increase speed to high for 1 minute.
Stir in balance of flour, a half cup at a time.
The dough will leave the sides of the bowl.
If the dough is moist and sticky, add a few sprinkles of flour.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Beat yolks of eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Just before baking, add butter and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Use hot griddle.
For thick cakes, use 1 to 1 1/3 cups milk

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; add margarine.
Cook onions in water.
Melt cheese, soup and milk until creamy (over low heat).
Mix softened onions with cream sauce.
Pour broccoli in casserole dish; pour onion/cheese sauce over it and crush crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue lexington style
directions: Sear the roast on all sides in lightly greased skillet.
Put meat, sugar, salt and vinegar in crock-pot and cook 10 to 12 hours or until well done. Remove meat from crock-pot.
Remove bones and cut into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce and toss with meat.

title: low cholesterol dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine oil, hot water and honey.
In small bowl, combine beaten whites, salt and skim milk.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add contents of small bowl to large bowl mixture, then add yeast.
Stir in 6 cups of flour; knead until smooth and elastic, adding flour as needed to make dough smooth.
Lightly smooth top of dough with oil.
Cover with cloth; let rise until double in size.
Punch down and shape rolls as desired.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double again.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Spread the inside of pie shell with mustard for flavor.
Saute onion in butter and seasonings.
Add zucchini and cook until tender.

title: dilly french loaf
directions: Stir together softened butter or margarine and dill weed. Slice bread in 1-inch slices, cutting to but not through bottom crust.
Spread dill butter between slices. Wrap loaf in heavy foil.
Heat for 20 to 30 minutes or grill over low coals, turning loaf frequently.

title: macaroons
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, water and Cheez Whiz until melted.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and add rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled for larger batch.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter, add flour gradually.
Add sugar, nuts and flavoring.
Press into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Press into powdered sugar while warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine broth, broccoli and onion in 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in evaporated milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Heat slowly to serving temperature.
Do not boil. Serves 4.

title: low fat lime pie
directions: Dissolve Jello in the boiling water.
Mix in yogurt.
On low speed, mix in whipped topping until smooth.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: easy chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Ziploc bag.
Place chicken in bag; rub marinade all over chicken.
Close Ziploc bag tightly, removing as much air as possible.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour, then broil, bake or barbecue chicken until cooked completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and water in a 2-quart casserole; cover and microwave at High 4 minutes.
Drain.
Place broccoli in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Spoon mixture over broccoli.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Rotate dish; microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan lamb chops
directions: In shallow bowl with fork, lightly beat egg white.
Add mustard; beat until blended.
Set aside.
On waxed
paper, combine pecans, bread crumbs and garlic.
Set aside.

title: chocolate nut fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, butter or margarine, marshmallow cream and Pet evaporated milk.
Cook and stir to a full all over boil (mixture will be bubbly all over the top). Boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in nuts and pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into about 30 pieces.

title: wrapped bacon sandwich
directions: Fry tortilla in frying pan until puffy.
Take out and wrap tortilla in a moist towel, microwave for 10 seconds.
Remove paper towel and place tortilla on a plate.
Place 2 slices of bacon, 3 slices of ham, rest of bacon, pickles, tomatoes and onions.
Add ranch dressing and wrap it up.
Serve while warm.

title: green bean dish
directions: Mix together potatoes, wieners, onion and beans.
Place in a casserole dish.
Heat milk enough to melt cheese.
Add flour and salt.
Place sauce over potato mixture and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: red satin party punch
directions: Combine all liquids.
This is so simple yet so tasty and colorful.
Be sure to make ice out of 7-Up and not water.
Makes 30 (4 ounce) cups.

title: whole wheat health bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf tin.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in yogurt, molasses or honey.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: I grate the potato until it gets to a small piece, then I toss the end in the blender.
Put the onion in the blender, too.
Also the eggs.
Stir all together in a large bowl.
Double recipe as needed.
About 8 cups of potatoes are enough for 4 good appetites. Fry in small amount of shortening or oil.
Brown well and turn to cook.
Serve with syrup, or my favorite is grape jelly.
Re-warms well the next day if there are any leftovers.

title: "stained glass" paintbrush cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide dough and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on well floured pastry cloth.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°, until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook 1 package of pasta until done.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Put back in pan and add dressings.
Mix well and add vegetables.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: Layer ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not peek.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix and bake in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk and chilies together.
Tear tortillas into 2-inch pieces.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese in that order twice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: 300 dollar cake
directions: Mix cocoa with a little water first.
Mix oil and margarine and cook 1 minute.
Mix flour and sugar together and add chocolate mixture that is cool.
Add eggs and buttermilk and soda mixed together.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Lightly cook and drain zucchini that has been peeled and cut in squares.
Mix dressing and butter.
Mix all ingredients with half of dressing mixture.
Put in casserole and top with remaining dressing.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: confidential chat fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until brown, remove.
Slightly beat eggs and fry in same pan, breaking up. Add rice and fry 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Add chicken, pork or shrimp, bean sprouts, onions, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown in skillet the meat, celery, onion, garlic and water. Cover, steam until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Drain.
Add to meat along with soup, undrained mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Spread into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in cold oven.
Set at low heat (250°).
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: eileen's tomato soup
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until done, then sieve.
Add the sugar, pepper and salt.
Melt the butter.
Add the flour.
Add tomato mixture and cook for 10 minutes.
May be frozen in individual servings or put in jars and processed.

title: incredible edible(pancakes)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Must use cast-iron skillet.
In a mixing bowl, lightly whip eggs and milk.
Add flour gradually. Then add sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Melt butter in skillet and coat bottom and sides.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: knott's cabbage with ham
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, pour in water and then add cabbage and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 4 minutes or until just tender.
Drain almost all of the liquid; then add ham and toss well.
Serve in a side dish to accompany fried chicken.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wilma's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; grate cheese, garlic and parsley very fine like dust.
Roll meat into balls, put on oiled cookie sheet with water added to oil.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: paul's everyday wheat bread
directions: For Bread Machine:
Add all ingredients in the order recommended by manufacturer.
Press "start" button.
Use white or whole wheat setting.

title: deviled ham and cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Serve with crackers.

title: vanilla butter nut cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, margarine and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour. Fold flavoring in by hand.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Wash, dry and cut okra into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook okra 5 minutes in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes in covered pan.
Stir in bacon 3 to 4 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems from caps.
Brush caps with some oil and place in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy 4-quart saucepan; add flour.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly; remove from heat.
Gradually blend in broth.
Add broccoli, carrots, celery, onion, salt, garlic powder and thyme.
Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: braised chicken with sour cream
directions: Rub chicken with lemon juice.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper. Brown chicken in oleo.
Place in baking dish. Add remaining ingredients and cover with sour cream. Cover and cook in slow oven at 325° until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle
with cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Add one egg at a time and add one cup of flour in at a time. Set oven on 375° and bake for an hour and a half or two hours.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring; mix well.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry; gently fold into sweetened condensed milk mixture.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with whipped topping and reserved crumbs before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: garden spread
directions: Let cream cheese sit out at room temperature until soft before mixing.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat 2 quarts cider with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Strain into remaining 2 quarts cold cider.
Serve warm.

title: ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prick pie crusts with fork to prevent gas bubbles.
Place a layer of ham and then cheese in the bottom of each crust.
Mix well the dry milk powder and water.
Mix in all other ingredients except paprika.
Pour into the crusts and sprinkle paprika on top. Bake until brown on top and custard is firm.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in well-greased dish.
Cover with topping.

title: jumbo fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix brownie mix, flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in chips. Drop cookie dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls, 3-inches apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or just until set and tops of cookies are dry.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes and remove from sheet. Makes about 15.
Regular size:
Drop by tablespoon and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Mix together meat, bread crumbs, paprika, salt, pepper and onions.
Spread in a greased baking dish.
Add chopped olives and sprinkle over meat.
Pour tomato soup on top of mixture.
(I use a knife and make slits in mixture so soup will penetrate.)
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit. Slice bananas (sprinkle lemon juice over bananas to keep from turning dark).
Reserve pineapple juice. Combine pineapple juice, pudding mix and Tang. Combine fruit and dressing. Toss gently.
Chill.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine and freeze in cups.

title: mincemeat
directions: Put into a large kettle:
chopped beef, suet, brown sugar, molasses, cider, currants, raisins and citron.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until the sugar and citron melt.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Fill cupcake papers 2/3 full and bake at 350° until golden brown (approximately 12 to 15 minutes).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg, slightly beaten.
Add a little flour.
Stir well.
Continue in same manner until all eggs and flour have been added.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour into lightly greased tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 375° or until cake is golden brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cottage cheese, 1 cup canned milk, salad dressing, crushed pineapple and black walnuts. Put in mold and let stay in refrigerator to cool.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to pumpkin mixture and stir.
Add nuts or raisins. Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold apple mixture into dressing, then fold in whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookie treat
directions: Pour milk into a bowl.
Take 1 cookie at a time and dip both sides into the milk quickly.
Don't leave it in the milk because it will become soggy.
Layer dipped cookies in the bottom of a dish. Now put whipped cream on top of the layer.
Alternate cookies and whipped cream layers.
Finish with whipped cream.
Add nuts.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Enjoy.

title: dr. malley's orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and one cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg yolks.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add them alternately with the sour cream, stirring until smooth.
Stir in the orange rind and the chopped nuts.
Beat the egg whites until stiff (but not dry) and fold into batter.
Grease a 9-inch tube cake pan and pour in the batter.
Bake 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture, alternately with water. Stir in raisin and nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in freezer.
Will make a pitcher full.
This makes its own slush.
Freeze 24 hours.
When ready to serve, fill glass half full of slush and finish with 7-Up.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Beat in blender or mixer until stiff.

title: pull apart cake
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Mix brown sugar and pecans.
Melt butter.
Dip biscuits in butter.
Roll in brown sugar and pecan mix.
Lay biscuits in Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pull apart and eat.

title: ham, shrimp and rice
directions: Combine shrimp, ham, soy sauce, peanut oil and ginger root. Let stand 10 minutes.
Place rice in a 2-quart saucepan with tight-fitting lid.
Add water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Lower heat to medium.
When all of the water and bubbles have disappeared from the surface of the rice, lower heat to simmer.
Place shrimp and ham mixture on top of rice.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add the bell pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: heavenly berried chocolate mousse pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate morsels.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add brown sugar, vanilla and cooled chocolate.
Mix well.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into pie crust and chill 8 hours.
Arrange sliced strawberries on top and drizzle with remaining chocolate and shortening, that has been melted.

title: rotel meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine first 7 ingredients and spread into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain excess drippings. Spoon chili sauce over cooked meat loaf.
Then, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: unmixed cherry delight
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle sugar over the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of sugar and cherries.
Slice oleo thin and lay on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is slightly brown and filling bubbly.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Blend dried beef in blender; add 3/4 of it to all the other ingredients.
Roll the ball in the 1/4 that was left.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water.
Place in saucepan with 2-inches of water.
Add small sliced onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 35 minutes.
Remove chicken to a large bowl and refrigerate.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart covered casserole, combine beans, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add seasoning mix and stir well.
Fold in onions.
Cover and microwave on High for a total of 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Remove and serve hot.
Dip may be kept hot in crock-pot or fondue pot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Dip may also be made in advance and refrigerated, then reheated to serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage noodles
directions: Trim and shred cabbage.
Place in bowl and salt and pepper. Toss to distribute evenly.
Leave it rest for 1 hour.
Squeeze to remove liquid.
Melt butter in pan and saute onions until light brown.
Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Take care not to let it burn.

title: creme de cacao torte
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, blending just until combined.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Sprinkle each layer with one tablespoon creme de cacao.
Cool completely.
Meanwhile, prepare creme de cacao filling.

title: stuffed tomato
directions: Mix together; stuff tomatoes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
While still beating, add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, vanilla and flour.
Bake in four layers using 8-inch well-greased and floured pans.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake until brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well; add vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Fold into margarine mixture.
Roll on floured board or roll it in your hand and flatten.
Cook at 350° for about 12 minutes.
I like them better without nuts.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Form in walnut size balls. Chill.
Melt 1/4 cake paraffin with 12 ounces chocolate chips.
Dip balls 3/4 way into chocolate.
Place undipped side on wax paper. Chill.

title: instant peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put peanut butter, sugar, vanilla and egg in mixing bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Space 2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and water together.
Add all the dry ingredients and beat until smooth about 2 minutes.
Stir in apples, rolled oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pat crescent roll dough on a greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine Miracle Whip, cream cheese and spices.
Beat until creamy.
Spread on cooled crust. Chop onions including tops and bell pepper.
Shred carrots.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerettes and slice very thin. Slice olives for garnish.
Distribute evenly all vegetables over top of cream cheese mixture; add Cheddar cheese and press down into pizza and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: swedish potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, with peels on, until tender, but firm.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Melt margarine.
Add cream of chicken soup, onion and Cheez Whiz.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Mix sauce gently into grated potatoes.
Put in baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not add salt!!!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and up sides.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put chopped pecans on bottom of pie crust.
Combine other ingredients to make filling and pour on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts wellington(easy and tastes great!)
directions: *It comes frozen in a 17 1/4 ounce box (2 sheets).

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in serving dish and refrigerate.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Whip 1 pint cream.
Line a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with wax paper.
Lay ladyfingers flat on bottom and stand around edges.

title: french-fried potato salad
directions: Pour 4 cups water into large saucepan; bring to full rolling boil.
Carefully drop frozen potatoes in water.
Remove from heat immediately.
Cover and let stand for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain potatoes at once; spread on paper towel.
Cut up any large pieces. Sprinkle with salt and cool.
In bowl, combine eggs, radishes, celery, onion and parsley.
Add mayonnaise and vinegar.
Add potatoes and toss gently.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour dough biscuits
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in hot water.
Mix all dry ingredients and add shortening, yeast and butter milk.
Knead.
Let sit 2-3 hours to rise.
Roll out desired amount of dough to 1/4 inch thickness. Fold over and cut with cutter.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes, until just begining to brown.
Remainder of dough may be refrigerated and will keep approximately 2 weeks.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple juice and set pineapple and juice aside.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter and sprinkle crumbs and mix.
Press crumbs into bottom of pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven (or 325° for glass dish) for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions in a large frying pan and drain off excess grease. Cut tortillas into fourths and layer in the bottom of a greased glass 9X13 baking dish.

title: california gourmet garlic loaf
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Place halves on foil covered baking sheet.
Tear out soft inner portion of bread in large chunks.
Melt butter in large skillet and stir in garlic and sesame seed.
Add bread chunks and fry until bread is golden and butter is absorbed.
Remove from heat.

title: bradford nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add honey and beat well.
Separate eggs and add well beaten yolks to mixture.
Add salt and vanilla. Add milk and flour; beat mixture well and add pecans and walnuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: chocolate-zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-cup (2 liter) Bundt pan. Put nuts into blender container.
Cover and process 2 cycles at chop or until coarsely chopped.
Empty container and set aside.

title: lemon lime punch
directions: Mix together with enough water to make 1 quart.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; arrange in buttered dish.
Make layers of potatoes, soup, butter and onion.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Warm soup and cream cheese until cheese is dissolved.
Dissolve Knox in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add Knox to soup mix.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: angel halos
directions: Sift together and set aside the dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening and packed brown sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator to chill while preparing next step.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Melt oleo separately and add water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture. Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla. Mix and pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: miss-gulf coast pralines
directions: In saucepan, add brown sugar, water and butter; mix well. Place over low heat until bubbles appear.
Add 1/2 pound chopped or halved pecans and remove from heat; stir until thick, then dip by tablespoons quickly on wax paper.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine tomato, cucumber, green pepper, artichoke, and pasta; toss lightly.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper together.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomatoes, oregano and bay leaves.
Simmer, covered, at least 2 hours or until cooked down.
Stir often.
Boil 1 package of lasagna noodles; blanch and drain.
Grease a large 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Pour over steak a mixture of celery soup, onion soup mix and milk.
Bake tightly covered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of 8 x 8 baking dish. Stir together dry pudding mix and lemonade mix in medium bowl. Add milk and mix or whisk together. Fold in 3/4 of the Cool Whip. Pour into dish and top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill until ready to serve. Serves 8.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thick enough potatoes to fill your crock-pot. Add chopped onion among the potatoes if you wish.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain off the water.
(You might wish to save it for gravy or soup.) Melt Velveeta cheese, cheese soup and margarine in microwave, stirring occasionally.
Pour this over the drained potatoes and continue to heat on low heat.

title: beef brisket
directions: Make a leakproof bed.
Use heavy foil.
Put brisket in foil and sprinkle Accent and spread Kitchen Bouquet on top.
Mix 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce and 3/4 cup ketchup and spread over brisket.
Sprinkle minced garlic and pepper on top.
Wrap tightly and place foil-wrapped brisket in roasting pan.
Bake 3 to 4 hours at 325°.
Pour gravy to use with serving and slice meat across the grain.
Microwave 1 minute on platter before serving to warm.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Melt fat in frying pan.
Brown onion and okra slightly, stirring as it cooks.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook over moderate heat until vegetables are tender and mixture is thick, about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Season with more salt and pepper, if needed.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Cut out with biscuit cutter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions on box.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
After cake cools, crumble enough cake in bottom of punch bowl to cover it.
Then top with cherry pie filling, pineapple and then bananas.
Pour enough pudding on top to cover.
Continue repeating layers until all gone.
End with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: clam cakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; put into refrigerator for a while until firm.
Take out and make into patties; roll in corn flake crumbs and deep fry until golden brown.

title: tea cakes (cookies)
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour gradually.
Mix well.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut desired shape.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen tea cakes.

title: syrup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in buttermilk and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add to syrup mixture and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: I most always use more meat, cheese, onion and peppers to suit ones taste.

title: peggy o's baked beans
directions: Fry strips of bacon and save grease.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add bacon and some grease.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: pineapple braised chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and dry on paper towel.
Combine flour with pinch of salt and pepper. Roll chicken in mixture.
Saute chicken in hot oil in skillet until golden brown.
Drain.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Saute garlic, onion and pepper until tender. Drain pineapple and oranges.
Reserve juices.
Add mustard, soy sauce, chili sauce and juices. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until thick (about 5 minutes).
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and oranges, basting with liquid in casserole. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until
chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: mom's chutney cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except almonds and additional chutney, in a food processor.
Garnish with remaining chutney and almonds.
Best if made the day before serving. Serve with plain crackers.

title: spiced applesauce-raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Crush cereal.
Mix all ingredients except raisins in large bowl; beat 30 seconds.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into pan. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until done.
Add spices, then remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except the beef; mix well.
Add ground beef.
Mix lightly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour; drain and let stand 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: fast and easy chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla, water, peanut butter and eggs until fluffy. Blend flour into mixture.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken breast dressing
directions: Simmer chicken in oil and water.
Cook until tender.
Cut up chicken; mix together with vegetables.
Mix bread crumbs and chicken broth together.
Mix all together.
Pour into baking dish. Bake in 325° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, water and undiluted soup.
Add chicken, onion, pepper, almonds, rice, salt to taste and chopped eggs.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; top with crushed potato chips. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 10.

title: thelma's grated apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake until crust is brown.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curry
directions: Simmer onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add flour, curry powder and salt.
Blend well and add tomato juice, cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mix comes to a boil.
Add turkey and let come to a boil again.
Reduce heat to a simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add beef and salt; cook until brown.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: my chili
directions: Mix ingredients and let boil; add cheese, if desired.

title: garlic feta cheese spread
directions: In food processor (or with beaters), blend together all the ingredients until combined. Transfer to serving bowl and chill it, covered, 2 hours. Spread on crisp crackers or bagel chips. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook enough cornbread to make 1/2 gallon.
Boil chicken breasts.
Save 7 1/2 cups of broth (add water if needed).
Crumble bread; add onion, pepper, sage, salt and chicken.
Toss until well mixed.
Place into a 4-quart baking dish or oven pan.
Add margarine and cream of chicken soup to broth; heat and stir until soup is dissolved.
Pour over bread mixture.
Stir very little. Bake in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: never fail divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and boil for 2 minutes. Uncover.
Cook until soft ball.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Saute the onion in 1/4 cup margarine.
Mix drained potatoes, onion, sour cream, salt, cheese and pepper together and put in a baking dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter and cover in grated cheese.
Bake until the cheese is bubbly at 350°.

title: oven pancakes
directions: This is a Christmas Eve tradition for our family.

title: super energy bars
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add peanut butter and keep stirring until blended.
Add marshmallows and stir constantly until all are melted.
(Or melt butter, peanut butter and marshmallows in large microwave bowl for 2 minutes.
Stir to blend and nuke another 1 to 2 minutes until all ingredients are melted.)
Mix crispy cereal, rolled oats and peanuts in a bowl. Stir into melted mixture.
Add chocolate candies at the very end of the blending process.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and press mixture into pan with buttered hands.
Let cool.
Cut into bars and wrap in plastic wrap or store in freezer in plastic bags. Makes 24 bars or 48 cookies.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish with 1/4 cup of butter.
Place into oven until dish is hot and margarine is melted.
Mix picante sauce into cut-up biscuits.
Pour into dish.
Top with olives, onion, pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: fruit punch slush
directions: Blend bananas and juice concentrates in blender until smooth. Combine remaining ingredients, except lemon-lime.
Mix well in a large bowl.
Put into containers to freeze (may be placed in 2 containers).
Thaw slightly before serving.
Pour lemon-lime soda over fruit mix.
Should be slushy.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in bananas. Add flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer.
Spoon in 8 ounce Cool Whip until well blended.
Put in pie shell and cool in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pecan cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, thoroughly cream butter and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Cream until light; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add all extracts; beat until light.
Stir together flour and baking soda; add flour alternately with sour cream.
Add chopped nuts to beaten egg mixture.
Beat egg whites, adding remaining sugar.
When egg whites form soft peaks, fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes or until done.

title: southwestern stir-fry(heart healthy)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine juices, chili powder, oregano, garlic and cornstarch.
Add meat.
Mix well and marinate, refrigerated, for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Heat half of oil in a wok or large skillet.
Add onion and peppers. Stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Remove and keep warm. Add remaining oil, then stir-fry beef until just browned.
Stir in kidney beans, corn, tomato wedges, reserved vegetables and reserved marinade.
Stir gently until warmed through and sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve garnished with chopped cilantro.

title: blueberry cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup of flour with dark brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes and remove from oven.
In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium speed, beat together cream cheese and sugar just until combined.
Beat in remaining 2 tablespoons flour, the eggs, lemon juice and vanilla just until combined.
Pour over partially baked crust.
Drop spoonfuls of blueberry preserves over the top.
With back of small spoon, lightly swirl in preserves.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Turn off oven; prop open oven door.
Let cheesecake cool in oven for 10 minutes.
Cut with wet knife into 2-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Simmer clams, celery, potatoes, onions and salt slowly until soft bubbles appear, then add butter and pepper.
Let melt, then add remaining ingredients.
Let bubble slightly; serve.
Stir frequently while cooking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls in layers to cover bottom of pan and up 1/2 to 3/4-inch on sides.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool. Soften cream cheese.
Beat cream cheese with mayonnaise and dressing mix until fluffy.
Spread on baked pastry.
Add vegetables and top with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Save some cheese and crumbs for top.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Bring broth, water, onion, carrots and garlic to a boil in a 3 to 4-quart pot.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes, zucchini, green beans and pepper.
Return to boil.
Add pasta, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally until pasta is tender.
Stir in beans (kidney).

title: costa rican rice
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Combine into one pot.
Put 1/2 cup water into vegetables; cook vegetables until they boil.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Fry sausage until brown (scrambled); drain off grease.
Put sausage aside.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in same pan; heat oil.
Empty rice into hot oil. Lightly brown slowly.
Empty 2 cups water into rice; simmer slowly until done.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Core apples. Seed oranges.
Grind apples, oranges and cranberries.
This should make about 7 cups of pulp.
Mix with sugar and refrigerate.

title: apple braid(brunch)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent dough into 2 rectangles.
Place in greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan with long sides overlapping 1/2 inch; press perforation together to seal. Lightly sprinkle surface of dough with flour.
Pat dough out with fingers to form 13 x 7 inch rectangle.
In medium bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Cut apple slices into quarters;
Add to sugar mixture and toss lightly.
Place apple mixture in 2 inch wide strip lengthwise down center of dough to within 1/4 inch of each end.
Make cuts, 3/4 inch apart, on longest sides of rectangle just to edge of filling.
Braid dough by folding strips at an angle across apple mixture, alternating dough strips from one side to the other.
Fold top and bottom ends over; press to seal.
Brush with butter,
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.

title: cheese, rice, zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil.
Add zucchini and cook for a short time.
Layer the ingredients in buttered casserole using half of each ingredient; then repeat rice, soup, zucchini/onion mixture, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: light banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, margarine and applesauce. Blend in mashed bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda three times.
Fold into banana mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and milk in pan; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Put 2/3 of mix into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over mix.
Top with the rest of the mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, place sliced potatoes and onions.
Add water to cover and cook until potatoes are soft.
Use masher to break potatoes into smaller pieces.
Let simmer on low heat to boil down a bit.
Fry bacon until crisp and break into bits.
Add bacon, milk, corn, salt, pepper and parsley to potatoes.
Add some of the bacon drippings for flavor.
Heat thoroughly (do not boil).

title: marinade for poultry
directions: With a fork, combine olive oil, dry white wine and vinegar. Add garlic clove (minced), peppercorns, sweet basil (chopped) or tarragon and salt to taste.
Mix well.

title: oreo stuff
directions: Prepare pudding per package instructions.
Make sure there are no lumps.
Layer dish with Oreos, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat once more.
End with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle crushed Oreos on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into sticks.
Pour boiling water over and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain and pack in clean jars.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Beat confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese together. Set aside. Prepare chocolate pudding according to directions on box. Set aside until thickened and set. Pour cream cheese mixture into graham cracker crust. Top with chocolate pudding, then top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Serve.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five decker dinner
directions: Cover bottom of heavy pan with bacon.
Season Hamburger and make thick patties.
Place over bacon.
Slice potatoes 1/2 inch thick and place on top of burgers.
Slice onion 1/2
inch thick and place on top of potatoes.
Slice carrots and place over onions.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and cool.
In a bowl, combine egg salad, mayonnaise, mustard, onion and salt.
Stir in cooled potatoes, cover and chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate.
Drain shrimp and spread over cream cheese.
Spread seafood sauce evenly over shrimp.
Chill before serving.

title: clam dip
directions: Chop 1	teaspoon
of
onion very fine; set aside.
Open the can of
clams
and drain the clam juice into a small bowl. Save 2 tablespoons
of
the
juice
and
mix
in clams, cream cheese, onion
